iant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Common Holy Symbols</strong>:</span></p><h3>Worshippers</h3><h3>Holy Sites</h3><ul><li><p>Ocari Republic</p></li></ul><h3>Penances</h3><blockquote class=\"sidebar\"><h3 style=\"text-align:center\"><em><strong>Strictures</strong></em></h3><ul><li><em>Defend families and children from all harm</em></li><li><em>Life is sacred, do no harm lest another life is in danger</em></li><li><em>Never judge whom another loves.</em></li><li><em>Oppose the servants of the Unlooked for, wherever its misfortune arises.</em></li></ul></blockquote><h3>Blessings</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.FElNQGNiPzaOwwKT]{Blessing of Charisma}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.Cg2Q3TV66cpmheHS]{Blessing of Courage}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.OkKWAfnMiHfxhTnB]{Blessing of Finesse}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.iIfYOlNrLb0uiV8c]{Blessing of Fortune}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.K5DE9cceinUTIrem]{Blessing of Protection}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.tMocig1z9dHKNiCT]{Blessing of Wit}</p><h3>Miracles</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.SItGUVYokyOo7csk]{Unblemished Innocence}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.rRq3FMkHaKO26fXP]{Yondalla's Rage}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.pBWXlJDOE7tfl8hP]{Yondalla's Succour}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.dDxhGgBBM9CugxsH]{Yondalla's Union}</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":462500,"name":"Cult of Haendryk, the Merchant of Jewels","type":"text","_id":"gk6H2QtLQMWgkwLh","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Seat of Power</strong>:</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;font-family:CaslonPro;font-weight:500;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);background:none;border:none;width:558px;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Head of the Cult</strong>: Arch-Priestess Ariniana Goldstone, Haendryk’s Greatest Worldy Profit</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;font-family:CaslonPro;font-weight:500;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);background:none;border:none;width:558px;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Primary Orders</strong>:</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;font-family:CaslonPro;font-weight:500;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);background:none;border:none;width:558px;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Major Festivals</strong>: None, though Smith's day is seen as a sacred day</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;font-family:CaslonPro;font-weight:500;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);background:none;border:none;width:558px;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Popular Holy Books</strong>: All those which Gleam</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;font-family:CaslonPro;font-weight:500;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);background:none;border:none;width:558px;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Common Holy Symbols</strong>: A gemstone, A coin without insignia, clasped hands, a warehouse with open doors</span></p><h3>Worshippers</h3><p>Haendryk's cult attracts anyone concerned with trade and coin. Merchants are his primary supplicants, but those who work with gold, such as jewellers, also honour him, while caravan guards pray to him to protect their charges.</p><p>Minting houses, banks, and well-established shops have shrines to Haendryk kept on a shelf. The first coin made each day is considered Haendryk’s, and is placed on the altar in the belief that what is given to the god will be returned twice over.</p><p>It is rare to find followers among the lower classes. Instead, the cult recruits from established merchant families or guilds. Many such families seek positions for their young scions to secure favourable treatment, and the cult accepts anyone for a fee.</p><h3>Holy Sites</h3><h3>Penances</h3><blockquote class=\"sidebar\"><h3 style=\"text-align:center\"><em><strong>Strictures</strong></em></h3><ul><li>No day without Profit</li><li>Deal in Truth</li><li>Help those who help themselves</li><li>Always get the best deal</li></ul></blockquote><p><em><strong>No Day Without Profit</strong></em></p><p>A follower of Haendryk must ensure the day is profitable. Coin is preferred, but profit can mean many things depending on the person. The important thing is the worshipper should act for their own net gain, whether this be closing an important trade deal, or getting one’s fellows to buy the next round of drinks. It is understood that the greater a person’s station, the more Haendryk demands of this stricture.</p><p><em><strong>Deal in Truth</strong></em></p><p>The Cult of Haendryk forbids false dealing, as trickery erodes the trust all trade is based upon. Followers cannot obscure the value of their wares, nor sell something they have no right to. </p><p>While they must deal truthfully, this is not the same as dealing honestly. Followers are free to exaggerate benefits, neglect to mention complications, or use information at their disposal to get the upper hand. Lying to gain an advantage would be in violation of this stricture, but using insider knowledge of a competitor’s financial situation would not.</p><p><em><strong>Help Those Who Help Themselves</strong></em></p><p>Haendryk earned his godhood and looks down on anyone not willing to do the same. While Haendryk ’s followers are called to share their earnings to benefit society, it must not be in a way which Haendryk views as encouraging laziness.</p><p>A priest of Haendryk would never give a beggar money for shelter, for example. Instead, they might direct them to a workhouse to earn their keep and contribute to the running of the institution.</p><p>Some in the cult interpret this as a condemnation of taxation, which they view as governments taking money not rightfully theirs. They fulfil this stricture by lobbying political figures to enact tax cuts, allowing them to distribute their money as they see fit.</p><p><em><strong>Always Get the Best Deal</strong></em></p><p>Trading is a holy act, a pure competition of wits with only one victor. Therefore, a follower of Haendryk must always get the best possible deal, regardless of circumstances. If a person is looking to buy grain, they must pay for it. The fact that their village is starving should not warrant merciful treatment.</p><p>However, the best deal does not always mean the most profitable. After all, if you take everything a person has, then who will trade with you next time? Sometimes, the best deal is one which builds relationships and leaves everyone happy, so that more profit can be extracted in the future.</p><h3>Blessings</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.FElNQGNiPzaOwwKT]{Blessing of Charisma}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.OkKWAfnMiHfxhTnB]{Blessing of Finesse}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.iIfYOlNrLb0uiV8c]{Blessing of Fortune}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.maUl7MoLvuvTOhM0]{Blessing of Grace}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.FRkIz2sR7ZC92W2G]{Blessing of Wisdom}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.prayers.tMocig1z9dHKNiCT]{Blessing of Wit}</p><h3>Miracles</h3><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.ldaHnrniXJcziDOc]{A Deal's a Deal}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.wwn69Zyn6y7REWl5]{Carry my Burdens}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.dkhnbUvY58WxQRlz]{Shake on It}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.B4ktmIHnf54cA4hS]{Supply and Demand}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.prayers.VCYKZNfu5VgfHCmK]{Trickle Down}</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":425000,"name":"Cult of Beory, the Earthmother","type":"text","_id":"YJiSPPS80hBilYsJ","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Seat of Power</strong>:</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;font-family:CaslonPro;font-weight:500;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);background:none;border:none;width:558px;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Head of the Cult</strong>:</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;font-family:CaslonPro;font-weight:500;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);background:none;border:none;width:558px;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-color:initial;text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonPro\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Primary Orders</strong>:</span></p><p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;margin:0.5em 0px;font-family:CaslonPro;font-weight:500;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);background:none;border:none;width:558px;font-siz