/p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Legs</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:32.0506%\"><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.i76oPVM2eFEs5IBh]{Mail Coat}</em></p></td><td style=\"width:13.304%;text-align:center\"><p><em>3GC</em></p></td><td style=\"width:5.16767%;text-align:center\"><p><em>3</em></p></td><td style=\"width:6.59703%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Common</em></p></td><td style=\"width:19.1387%;text-align:center\"><p><em>-</em></p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Arms, Body</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:32.0506%\"><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.4xV16ttsxCa311vl]{Mail Coif}</em></p></td><td style=\"width:13.304%;text-align:center\"><p><em>1GC</em></p></td><td style=\"width:5.16767%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td><td style=\"width:6.59703%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Scarce</em></p></td><td style=\"width:19.1387%;text-align:center\"><p><em>-10% Perception</em></p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Head</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:32.0506%\"><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.cJdfHOVbghTf4Eo0]{Mail Shirt}</em></p></td><td style=\"width:13.304%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2GC</em></p></td><td style=\"width:5.16767%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td><td style=\"width:6.59703%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Scarce</em></p></td><td style=\"width:19.1387%;text-align:center\"><p><em>-</em></p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Body</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:100%;text-align:center\" colspan=\"7\"><p style=\"text-align:center;font-family:CaslonAntique;font-size:var(--font-size-18);margin:0px\"><em><strong><span style=\"font-family:CaslonAntique\"><span style=\"font-family:CaslonAntique\">PLATE**</span></span></strong></em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:32.0506%\"><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.oBNXxRFPh1sOT4K2]{Plate Breastplate}</em></p></td><td style=\"width:13.304%;text-align:center\"><p><em>10GC</em></p></td><td style=\"width:5.16767%;text-align:center\"><p><em>3</em></p></td><td style=\"width:6.59703%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Scarce</em></p></td><td style=\"width:19.1387%;text-align:center\"><p><em>-</em></p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Body</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:32.0506%\"><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.TvUKzvXjc2VChuTT]{Plate Open Helm}</em></p></td><td style=\"width:13.304%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2GC</em></p></td><td style=\"width:5.16767%;text-align:center\"><p><em>1</em></p></td><td style=\"width:6.59703%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Common</em></p></td><td style=\"width:19.1387%;text-align:center\"><p><em>-10% Perception</em></p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Head</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:32.0506%\"><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.oW7wSkl4JMb5sBH8]{Plate Bracers}</em></p></td><td style=\"width:13.304%;text-align:center\"><p><em>8GC</em></p></td><td style=\"width:5.16767%;text-align:center\"><p><em>3</em></p></td><td style=\"width:6.59703%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Rare</em></p></td><td style=\"width:19.1387%;text-align:center\"><p><em>-</em></p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Arms</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:32.0506%\"><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.bY6M9XxbqmFmqpA8]{Plate Leggings}</em></p></td><td style=\"width:13.304%;text-align:center\"><p><em>10GC</em></p></td><td style=\"width:5.16767%;text-align:center\"><p><em>3</em></p></td><td style=\"width:6.59703%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Rare</em></p></td><td style=\"width:19.1387%;text-align:center\"><p><em>-10% Stealth</em></p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Legs</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr><tr><td style=\"width:32.0506%\"><p><em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.e9WmLbD7AuXSeWp0]{Plate Helm}</em></p></td><td style=\"width:13.304%;text-align:center\"><p><em>3GC</em></p></td><td style=\"width:5.16767%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td><td style=\"width:6.59703%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Rare</em></p></td><td style=\"width:19.1387%;text-align:center\"><p><em>-20% Perception</em></p></td><td style=\"width:21.1032%;text-align:center\"><p><em>Head</em></p></td><td style=\"width:2.63881%;text-align:center\"><p><em>2</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>*Soft Leather can be worn without penalty under any other Armour</em></p><p><em>** Wearing any Mail or Plate confers a Penalty of -10 Stealth each</em></p></blockquote><h3>Armour Damage</h3><p>As blows rains down on your armour, it can be damaged, possibly permanently. Whenever you are instructed to damage a piece of armour, the APs in the location damaged are reduced by 1. </p><p>If this lowers the APs to 0 in that location, the armour there is rendered useless.</p><p>Armour is generally damaged in one of two ways: </p><ul><li><p>A special ability triggers, such as a spell or Talent, damaging a piece of armour</p></li><li><p>A Critical Wound is deflected</p></li></ul><h4>Critical Deflection</h4><p>This only occurs should you choose it to. If you suffer a Critical Wound from an incoming attack on a location protected by armour, you can choose to let your armour be damaged by 1AP in order to ignore the Critical Wound. </p><p>You still suffer all normal Wounds (and given your APs are now 1 point lower, you probably suffer an extra Wound), but you avoid the Critical Wound effects as the blow is absorbed by your now-damaged armour.</p><h4>Repairing Armour</h4><p>It costs 10% of the armour’s base price per AP lost to repair it. So, if you had a Sleeved Chainmail Coat with 1AP of damage on the Body, and 1AP of damage on the Arms, it will cost you 20% of your armour’s base cost to fix it, in this case 12/–. If a section of your armour is completely broken, it will cost you 30% of the armour’s base cost to fix, and you’ll likely be waiting some time before it’s completed. </p><p>You can also repair your own armour if you have the appropriate Trade Skill, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.OD83JAlc9KhDpHK5]{Trade Tools} and, for Plate Armour, a @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.ixOMVrEC1ISyYdDU]{Workshop}.</p><h3>Armour Qualities</h3><p>Armour can possess the following Armour Qualities:</p><h4>Flexible</h4><p>Flexible armour can be worn under a layer of non-Flexible armour if you wish. If you do so, you gain the benefit of both.</p><h4>Impenetrable</h4><p>The armour is especially resilient, meaning most attacks simply cannot penetrate it. All Critical Wounds caused by an odd number to hit you, such as 11 or 33, are ignored.</p><h3>Armour Flaws</h3><p>Some armours have points of weakness, as described by Armour Flaws.</p><h4>Partial</h4><p>The armour does not cover the entire hit location. An opponent that rolls an even number to hit, or rolls a @UUID[JournalEntry.NS3YGlJQxwTggjRX.JournalEntryPage.wmA76Q2zJJ9HrkvA#criticals]{Critical Hit}, ignores the partial armour’s APs.</p><h4>Weakpoints</h4><p>The armour has small weakpoints where a blade can slip in if your opponent is sufficiently skilled or lucky. If your opponent has a weapon with the @UUID[.wdXywmb7FBVipOw8#impale]{Impale} Quality and scores a Critical, the APs of your armour are ignored.</p>","markdown":""},"_id":"yYXaAw24i93B4vzk","image":{},"video":{"volume":0.5,"controls":true},"src":null,"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.10LxsWBSwEmjZWeV.JournalEntryPage.yYXaAw24i93B4vzk"}},"title":{"show":true,"level":2},"system":{}},{"name":"Packs and Containers","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Trappings can be packed into backpacks, sacks, and pouches, making them easier to carry. The table shows the Encumbrance value for carrying a pack or other container (<strong>Enc</strong>), and the number of Encumbrance the container can carry (<strong>Carries</strong>). You only count the <strong>Enc</strong> value to determine the number of Encumbrance points carried. Common sense dictates whether items can be carried in containers (e.g. halberds cannot be carried in backpacks).</p>\n<table style=\"width:99.0798%;height:224px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:58.9783%;height:16px;text-align:left\"><strong>Item</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:6.65635%;height:16px;text-align:center\"><strong>Cost</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:5.72755%;height:16px;text-align:center\"><strong>Enc</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:10.5263%;height:16px;text-align:center\"><strong>Carries</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:16.8731%;height:16px;text-align:center\"><strong>Availability</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:58.9783%;height:16px\">@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.kJziKlct30lfAiYA]{Backpack}</td>\n<td style=\"width:6.65635%;height:16px;text-align:center\">4/10</td>\n<td style=\"width:5.72755%;height:16px;text-align:center\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width:10.5263%;height:16px;text-align:center\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width:16.8731%;height:16px;text-align:center\">Common</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:16px\">\n<td style=\"width:58.9783%;height:16px\">@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.trappings.4hyL1z3ayI3ligQE]{Barrel}</td>\n<td style=\"width:6.65635%;height:16px;text-align:center\">8/-</td>\n<td style=\"width:5.72755%;height:16px;text-align:center\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width:10.5263%;height:16px;text