erbox}</td><td style=\"width:7.27554%;height:16px;text-align:center\">4/2</td><td style=\"width:6.19195%;height:16px;text-align:center\">0</td><td style=\"width:18.4211%;height:16px;text-align:center\">Common</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","markdown":""},"_id":"fiXbxW3H96StJWmH","image":{},"video":{"volume":0.5,"controls":true},"src":null,"sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.2Yn7wOvwiK7yIJcg.JournalEntryPage.fiXbxW3H96StJWmH"}},"title":{"show":true,"level":2},"system":{}},{"name":"Hirelings","type":"text","text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>If you need extra muscle or brains whilst adventuring, you may pay Hireling NPCs to accompany you. You can hire any Career with GM permission, and they are paid an amount of coin equal to their Social Status for a quick job, or paid triple for a full day’s work. The GM may increase or decrease this amount according to individual personality and local circumstances. </p><p>If the job at hand is unexpectedly dangerous, Hirelings will expect double the normal pay unless a Leadership Test is passed. Leadership Tests may also be required when Hirelings are assigned complex, independent tasks, or if they have good reason to flee from an encounter. Quick Hireling profiles are created by adding 5 Advances to every Career Characteristic and Skill per level of the Career hired, and 1 Talent per level. Hirelings with more experienced than this usually cost more.</p><h3>Sample Hirelings</h3><table style=\"width:99.0798%;height:194px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"width:16.1644%;height:17px;text-align:center\"><strong>Hireling</strong></td><td style=\"width:14.9489%;height:17px;text-align:center\"><strong>Quick Job</strong></td><td style=\"width:14.1082%;height:17px;text-align:center\"><strong>Daily Cost</strong></td><td style=\"width:11.9871%;height:17px;text-align:center\"><strong>Weekly Cost</strong></td><td style=\"width:41.553%;height:17px;text-align:center\"><strong>Notes</strong></td></tr><tr style=\"height:31px\"><td style=\"width:16.1644%;height:31px\">Local Scout</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.9489%;height:31px\">@Pay[5bp]{5d}</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.1082%;height:31px\">@Pay[15bp]{15d}</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:11.9871%;height:31px\"><p>@Pay[10ss]{10/-}</p></td><td style=\"width:41.553%;height:31px\">Works independently without Leadership Tests</td></tr><tr style=\"height:10px\"><td style=\"width:16.1644%;height:10px\">Seasoned Mercenary</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.9489%;height:10px\">@Pay[3ss]{3/-}</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.1082%;height:10px\">@Pay[9ss]{9/-}</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:11.9871%;height:10px\">@Pay[3gc12ss]{3GC 12/-}</td><td style=\"width:41.553%;height:10px\">Demands a share of loot in lieu of danger pay</td></tr><tr style=\"height:34px\"><td style=\"width:16.1644%;height:34px\">Lawyer</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.9489%;height:34px\">@Pay[3ss]{3/-}</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.1082%;height:34px\">@Pay[9ss]{9/-}</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:11.9871%;height:34px\">@Pay[3gc12ss]{3GC 12/-}</td><td style=\"width:41.553%;height:34px\">Drafting a simple legal document costs 2-4 shillings</td></tr><tr style=\"height:34px\"><td style=\"width:16.1644%;height:34px\">Porter</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.9489%;height:34px\"><span style=\"background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\">@Pay[1ss]{1/-}</span></td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.1082%;height:34px\"><span style=\"background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\">@Pay[3ss]{3/-}</span></td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:11.9871%;height:34px\">@Pay[1gc4ss]{1GC 4/-}</td><td style=\"width:41.553%;height:34px\">Carries 10 Encumbrance points</td></tr><tr style=\"height:34px\"><td style=\"width:16.1644%;height:34px\">Scribe</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.9489%;height:34px\">@Pay[2ss]{2/-}</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.1082%;height:34px\">@Pay[6ss]{6/-}</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:11.9871%;height:34px\">@Pay[2gc8ss]{2GC 8/-}</td><td style=\"width:41.553%;height:34px\">Also translates 1-2 other common languages</td></tr><tr style=\"height:34px\"><td style=\"width:16.1644%;height:34px\">Doktor</td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.9489%;height:34px\"><span style=\"background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\">@Pay[5ss]{5/-}</span></td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:14.1082%;height:34px\"><span style=\"background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)\">@Pay[15ss]{15/-}</span></td><td style=\"text-align:center;width:11.9871%;height:34px\">@Pay[5gc]{5 GC}</td><td style=\"width:41.553%;height:34px\">A single visit costs 4-6 shillings for medical attention</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Henchmen</h3><p>Henchmen are Hirelings, companions, friends, pets, or other NPCs that are effectively permanent members of your party. Unlike other NPCs, Henchmen should have full character sheets, just like a PC, and are typically attached to one player, either as an employee, friend, owner, or similar. The Henchmen earns half the XP of that player, rounding down, which the player may spend on the Henchman’s behalf. Henchmen not only make memorable allies, but should your character die, they can also make marvellous PC replacements instead of creating a new character.</p>","markdown":""},"_id":"oRi9uwMS1O9Ol6Hx","image":{},"video":{"volume":0.5,"controls":true},"src":null,"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.II6fTMi8Uhr0wrKu.JournalEntryPage.oRi9uwMS1O9Ol6Hx"}},"title":{"show":true,"level":2},"system":{}},{"sort":750000,"name":"Basic Weapons","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Basic weapons are those that are wielded in one hand and require relatively little training to grasp the basic use of (though advocates of these weapons insist that there is a subtlety to their im