strong>: Gold 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Politics)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.JLzJws09GMw9GWBV]{Coolheaded}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.epPBu7x6BRWp2PHG]{Dealmaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XU7D9CCmumuhqDUi]{Public Speaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.b4x1qEWcevX7xK58]{Schemer}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: 2 sets of Quality Courtly Garb, 200 GC, Fiefdom, Jewelry worth 200 GC, Signet Ring<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.huYKd0sYPnF4ReB0]{Noble Lord}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 7<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rt2rGSwFDCDHPh0A]{Track}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x8g3U68oi8XzWiYr]{Commanding Presence}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OROfMcVqRnZHINkU]{Wealthy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: 4 sets of Best Quality Courtly Garb, Quality Foil or Hand Mirror, 500 GC, Jewelry worth 500 GC, Province<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"t41abSTLeMAdLiWS","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":4900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Investigator","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘I regret to inform you that your husband is buried in Frau Kohl’s vegetable garden, beneath the turnips. That will be 6 shillings and 4 pence, please.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Hemlock Surelight, Elven Sleuth</em></p><p> ‘We can deduce from this splintered door the thief exited with assistance from a very large creature. But said creature couldn’t have descended the narrow stairwell. Tis leaves only two possible conclusions. Either it materialized from thin air, or else our thief is a shape-changer...’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Zavant Konniger, ‘Sage-Detective’</em></p><p> ‘As I am sure you know, I am the world’s greatest detective. You ‘ave ‘eard of Alphonse, no?’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-horned-rat.actors.qvHgWQ8HF3rn003M]{Alphonse Hercules de Gascoigne}, Diminutive Bretonnian Detective</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>Perceptive and suspicious, you probe deep into the heart of any crime, and find answers.</em></p><p>Most Investigators pursue cases involving stolen property, missing persons, or murders, although some research stories for the emerging newssheets, or even blackmail crime suspects for ‘hush money’. Investigative techniques include footprint tracking, cross-examination, deductive reasoning and — if necessary — breaking and entry. Where secular investigators operate on the edge of the law or for an institution like the watch of a Merchant House, religious investigators — most commonly serving Sigmar and Verena — follow stricter ethical codes.</p><p>Experienced Investigators cultivate matter-of-fact airs of sophistication to improve their credibility. Some Master Investigators sell themselves as ‘observation specialists’ possessing skills they claim cannot be learned. Considerable self-promotion is required to become one of the famous Detectives who receive job offers from across the Old World.</p><p>Investigators are sometimes hired to solve mysteries far too dangerous to tackle alone, which can be the informal creation of an adventuring party. Of course, the very nature of mysteries can result in each solved case leading to yet another mystery. Investigators may therefore enjoy steady employment, provided they’re able to identify willing customers for every new mystery they uncover.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/investigator.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Burgher</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Investigator Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.AQmofCPcdFZNXCV6]{Sleuth}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zkI6tIqbyAZvh0Th]{Stealth (Urban)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rt2rGSwFDCDHPh0A]{Track}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.wBhPFggGqIXwbx1r]{Alley Cat}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5KP9sOoLSGvj9EXp]{Beneath Notice}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.oQzTJEXUx28sCiH3]{Sharp}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Lantern, Lamp Oil, Journal, Quill and Ink<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.a5B7FYYaSarc95Xc]{Investigator}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.2LDCVJQWkTFszMok]{Lore (Law)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.jLyoyqwmBVPjRjhM]{Melee (Brawling)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.AkjRsazdAppqveZu]{Pick Lock}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rvd0S8Z0v2m0MHmD]{Sleight of Hand}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QsrXxGZiHjth7RMg]{Savvy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XSb3QVB9ipPBFt56]{Shadow}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jviOQmy0luQOySC2]{Tenacious}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Leather Jack, Hand Weapon, Magnifying Glass, Lockpick<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.jGYtrDe0sNACF2pB]{Master Investigator}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zv3IyoU2wkPZu8pD]{Bookish}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.wrpVYmdiIy1jPulc]{Break and Enter}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LPgjE0cexTVOBVCY]{Suave}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Assistant, Office<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.fiHq2JGODlbQRdKh]{Detective}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9h82z72XGo9tfgQS]{Acute Sense (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.kQbVFzsh4LbaIzHU]{Speedreader}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.V9N0LMnXf1WYseCL]{Tower of Memories}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Network of Informants, Spyglass<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"zLWmjUbUdAOfiV3F","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":3900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Riverwarden","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><div><div><div><p>‘So back in the day, when I was a riverwarden, Big Willi came round to tell me I had to leave a certain shipment alone. He said I should just let it through and everything would be alright. Of course, I was young, wasn’t I? I told the ship’s Master all about it. And was I rewarded for my honesty? Nah, Big Willi came round and beat me up, and the next day I was drummed out of the river patrol. They were all in it together, weren’t they?’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Nikki Schnelling, ex-riverwarden</em></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>Strong-backed and sure, you patrol the riverways in hunt of lawbreakers and troublemakers.</em></p><p>A clarion call across the waterways heralds the arrival of the Imperial River Patrol, a river-borne police force known as much for its harassing thugs as for its good work. Most riverside villages and inns set aside moorings for them as, without them, worse criminals would rule the waters. The overworked patrols concentrate on egregious crimes, resolving petty misdemeanors with spot fines. On major trade-routes, the patrols have larger vessels manned by ‘Shipswords’ trained to tackle larger threats like Greenskins or Trolls.</p><p>Some Riverwardens rarely see the water, instead manning remote outposts overlooking strategically important waters. Others crew fast riverboats charged to intercept smugglers in the night. The largest Riverwarden vessels are effectively sea-worthy warships, bristling with cannon and mortars, ready for almost any eventuality</p><p>A diligent Riverwarden, searching vessels and following up leads, might stumble across any sort of nefarious plot or sinister cargo. Riverwardens typically work month-long shifts, but this means they also have months off. Tis structure is ideal for adventuring: as a Riverwarden need not desert their post to pursue private matters, or even have to persuade their Sergeant that it is their duty to follow up crimes. They can head off, investigate, and be back long before their next cycle begins.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/riverwarden.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Halfling</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Riverfolk</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Riverwarden Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.RqHOwFXhYtTWKiNP]{River Recruit}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.KL4pCOqma5E7fLG4]{Row}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.n8IfmLt4kzMhIKIv]{Sail}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.hodHqFNKAmu40ajh]{Swim}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.4wnQc19allWlyOGe]{Strong Swimmer}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.FF41XPboORgyDNsv]{Strong Back}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Zf0vk2rjllpDh0Ua]{Very Strong}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.tlEg21DHMEJoWcJq]{Waterman}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Hand Weapon (Sword), Leather Jack, Uniform<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.CXSKOpjA7a2kqWSq]{Riverwarden}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Riverways)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.H2upcZ7q7qAPtPic]{Ranged (Blackpowder)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.r180vP86SlwyJc8W]{Criminal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0ep8BNMiZGVLTHpr]{Gunner}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1kgHcImgfyKI1IYp]{Fisherman}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jQmIu8P85tF0njmD]{Seasoned Traveller}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Lantern and Oil, Pistol with 10 shot, Shield<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.FOGWbyemEGAkK746]{Shipsword}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8pVzgPkgWpTJvfhG]{Fearless (Wreckers)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.E98mVLZgE8bX5vQW]{Hatred (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.WEH97InIX29nzgW1]{Pilot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Ij9N3G8jzxb4lrwy]{Sea Legs}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Grappling Hook, Helmet, Mail Shirt<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.VIEEddQ4IW7Fjq2b]{Shipsword Master}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.2LDCVJQWkTFszMok]{Lore (Law)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x8g3U68oi8XzWiYr]{Commanding Presence}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RbnrfHf7GSQap0ig]{Kingpin}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.afREA9q7v4Scuozn]{Orientation}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Patrol Boats and Crew, Symbol of Rank<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"ADHp81MC8050ngjm","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":6000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Merchant","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘If Nuln wants trade wars, so be it, I’ll see their river blockaded and raise taxes on guns. After all, the Emperor owes me a few favors...’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Leo van Haagen, Marienburg Merchant Prince</em></p><p> ‘How did I became a millionaire? Well, when I was a girl with only a pfennig to my name, I went to the local farmer and bought an apple. Ten I walked to the market and sold the apple for two pfennigs. The next day I bought two apples from the farmer and walked to the market again and sold the apples for four pfennigs. And so it went on, every day; I walked to the farm bought some apples, and then walked to the market to sell them at a profit. And by the time I was twenty-five years old, my grandfather died and left me a million crowns.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Johanna Sainzburg, Fresh Fruit Magnate</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>Shrewd and numerate, you buy low to sell high, making more money than most will ever see</em></p><p>Most Merchants trade in simple goods such as alcohol, textiles, woodcraft, and pottery. For the ambitious, rare exotic goods such as Dwarf gromril or Eastern spices command higher profits, but risk longer transport routes and require strong foreign contacts. Merchants cannot sell in most towns without approval from (and payments to) a Merchants’ Guild, powerful institutions rivalling the noble courts’ political inﬂuence. Local commerce is managed by Traders who ship goods between backwater villages and nearby towns.</p><p>Traders can join guilds by apprenticing under Master Merchants as junior business partners. Powerful Merchant Princes owning warehouses and sales offices in multiple cities enjoy the same status as minor nobles. In addition to trading, some Merchants also branch out into banking, moneylending, and investing.</p><p>Merchants share a certain kinship with adventurers, often hiring them over professional caravan guards. Adventurers are adaptable and enterprising by nature, making them ideal candidates for partnership in a trading company, bringing Merchants into contact with all manner of colorful characters.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/merchant.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Burgher</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Merchant Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.2aKiMpKfVnXWNfmy]{Trader}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.MXy22hFCgntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.iYan4z52v7HYM9u9]{Drive}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}</em><br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.77p3QRKgFWakkndF]{Blather}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.epPBu7x6BRWp2PHG]{Dealmaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LPgjE0cexTVOBVCY]{Suave}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Abacus, Mule and Cart, Canvas Tarpaulin, 3d10 Silver Shillings<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.eFMNueIi3zp6vs6e]{Merchant}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Guilder)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.34EBUkHQkrqF1sq7]{Briber}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.HIofcsDLjXGKzSZf]{Embezzle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Guilder)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QsrXxGZiHjth7RMg]{Savvy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Riverboat or 2 Wagons, Guild License, 20 GC<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.mE6PJ1yIScBu6Tye]{Master Merchant}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{ Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.61L9aX2z164cjm7K]{Language (Classical)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.D4JNPSl6VOpsVmSi]{Secret Signs (Guilder)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LzgxyMknSHjSkkeQ]{Cat-tongued}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5QcrpLQWWrsbKR79]{Numismatics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.oQzTJEXUx28sCiH3]{Sharp}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Town House with Servants, Warehouse, 100 GC<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.8llxzvd0M3P59ctr]{Merchant Prince}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.u0CFf3xwiyidD9T5]{Luck}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.b4x1qEWcevX7xK58]{Schemer}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OROfMcVqRnZHINkU]{Wealthy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: 2 Riverboats or 4 Wagons, Large Town Estate, 2 Warehouses, 1000 GC, Quality Clothing<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"h7GdfctKdjWL0Ejp","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":4400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Apothecary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘Look for this sigil: white mortar, black pestle. Don’t ask for our order without it or you’ll be reported to the Watch. And lad, don’t ever short our Apothecary; you’ll spend the rest of your days wondering if the next drink will be your last.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Kathe the Unseen, Assassin</em></p><p> </p><p>‘Human chemistry? As shoddy as their architecture! And just as likely to kill you! I asked for tonic after a hard night’s drinking. Had the ﬂux for a week!’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Torica Norrasdotr, Dwarf Merchant</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><p><em>Skilled in chemistry and concoctions, you create and sell medicine of all kinds</em></p><p> Apothecaries specialize in preparing pharmaceutical medication — commonly pills, draughts, and ointments – for sale to patients and doktors alike. Their workshops are filled with a dazzling array of bubbling alembics, overﬂowing beakers, worn mortar and pestles, and other physic-making paraphernalia. Some Apothecaries supplement their income selling illicit substances — from stimulants for desperate students, to hallucinogenic weirdroot for bored nobles or shady commissions from even shadier groups. Supplying these is lucrative, but also dangerous. Rare ingredients are expensive, so Apothecaries frequently have cash ﬂow problems, and journey the wilds to collect their own ingredients. Many take temporary employment with expeditions, mercenaries, or the military for extra coin.</p><p>Due to Physician Guild pressure, most towns ban Apothecaries from formally practicing medicine, but during play Apothecaries can easily fill the role of a healer. Indeed, they are versatile in this role because they can also identify dangerous and unusual substances the party may encounter, and even turn some into useful medicine.</p><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/apothecary.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Apothecary Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td s