 Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.fdq3RFSOKl5b3WzW]{Art (Writing)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Speeches)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zv3IyoU2wkPZu8pD]{Bookish}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LzgxyMknSHjSkkeQ]{Cat-tongued}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.oGbDwnLOn3isPJpO]{Impassioned Zeal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QsrXxGZiHjth7RMg]{Savvy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Office, Assistant (Student or Servant)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.vcHUiputmUcPem6f]{Judge}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x8g3U68oi8XzWiYr]{Commanding Presence}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RbnrfHf7GSQap0ig]{Kingpin}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Law)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OROfMcVqRnZHINkU]{Wealthy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Gavel, Ostentatious Wig<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"uIKbkjQpNUCGIQRv","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":4100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Advisor","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><p>‘Sigmar votes with Reikland for three. The dead Emperor, Mootland, and Reikland will vote the same way, taking Reikland to six. As you know, you need seven votes to become emperor. Given Ar’Ulric always votes for Middenheim, it’s highly unlikely the Imperial seat will return to Nuln while the House of Third Wilhelm ﬂourishes. Best hope for a daughter, your Grace. A marriageable one.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Krammond, Advisor to the Elector Count of Nuln, 2475 IC</em></p></blockquote><div style=\"font-style:normal\"><p> </p></div><p><em>Wise and well-informed, you provide advice and guidance so your employer prospers.</em></p><p style=\"font-style:normal\">  Advisors provide counsel to those they serve. Well-versed in the political and social conditions of their employer’s domain, they are privy to confidential and sensitive information. While many Advisors are born into their positions, others actively seek noble patronage as a path to wealth and power. Some young royals pick their university or childhood friends as their first Aide, trusting them to say what no one else will.</p><p style=\"font-style:normal\">Long years at court or in service to a lesser noble pave the way to the loftier heights of their careers. Many Advisors do not serve the nobility at all, instead lending their extensive capabilities to criminals, warlords, merchants, cults, or guilds.</p><p style=\"font-style:normal\">If there is something peculiar or dangerous happening within their employer’s domain, then an Advisor is well-placed to investigate. At the higher levels of the career, a Counsellor or Chancellor will have their own trusted staff they can rely on to look after matters if they take a short leave of absence. Advisors can approach different classes of people, including the most difficult to access, and they are already in a position where they are expected to ask questions on behalf of their employer.</p><p style=\"font-style:normal\"> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/advisor.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf, Wood Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Courtier</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Advisor Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.WBA0vgLdGsJ32ccS]{Aide}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.61L9aX2z164cjm7K]{Language (Classical)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Politics)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5KP9sOoLSGvj9EXp]{Beneath Notice}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8lSoPDGrmeTIaapm]{Gregarious}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Writing Kit<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.TolERlCR35zIf9G4]{Advisor}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.77p3QRKgFWakkndF]{Blather}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.r180vP86SlwyJc8W]{Criminal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.b4x1qEWcevX7xK58]{Schemer}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.aZavWXbSXVBmWeJi]{Supportive}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Livery<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.G9PT2bovEv02sVJJ]{Counsellor}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.qBm2fu3oMhxsDBNQ]{Entertain (Storytelling)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.41JhsSNW1Ttza3JK]{Argumentative}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.34EBUkHQkrqF1sq7]{Briber}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.hTgrGkWnmIR4xhVe]{Carouser}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LzgxyMknSHjSkkeQ]{Cat-tongued}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Clothing, Aide<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.SM95bBsq3ZUFo3YB]{Chancellor}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.DiP9cmbqUir3HkkK]{Lore (Heraldry)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-akoris.AkorisSkills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x8g3U68oi8XzWiYr]{Commanding Presence}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.HIofcsDLjXGKzSZf]{Embezzle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RbnrfHf7GSQap0ig]{Kingpin}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LPgjE0cexTVOBVCY]{Suave}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Riding Horse with Saddle and Harness, Quality Courtly Garb, Sta? of Advisors and Aides<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"pwth0cd20Vdp0B9G","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Charlatan","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><p>‘I’ve carried this across countless leagues from the highest towers of the Elves. See how it sparkles in the moonlight? Only magic can cause this inner light! Unbelievable as it may be, I must grudgingly part with it. For such power, any price is but a triﬂe!’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-eis.eisactors.Akw4KEOxJei6b0Hf]{Wolmar Rotte}, Con Man</em></p><p> ‘The last living heir of Lord Schwalb, you say? Hogwash! You’re the fifth ‘heir’ to call this afternoon! How much did you pay for that scrap of paper? Better yet, who’s the swindler what sold it to you?’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Gerold Behn, Irritated Butler</em></p></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>Unscrupulous and charming, you separate fools from their money; thankfully, there is no shortage of fools…</em></p><p> A Charlatan traffics in trust, yet profits in treachery. By preying on emotions and psychological weaknesses, Charlatans offer their ‘mark’ a prize that is too good to be true. Social privilege provides no protection, and even the loftiest citizens can fall victim to a skilled Charlatan. In addition to a knack for lying, a lack of conscience is also of benefit to Charlatans.</p><p> Charlatans include Swindlers, Con Artists, Gamblers, and other Scoundrels seeking to prey on the gullible. Halﬂings often operate distraction cons in small family groups. Young High Elves, slumming it with Humans, treat their cons as one big game, not motivated by profit, but to prove their superiority. Some experienced Charlatans work with artists, who forge documentation for a cut of any profits.</p><p> To avoid rousing suspicion, Charlatans rarely stay in one area for long. Few Swindlers openly admit to their calling, preferring instead to masquerade as anyone other than themselves. Because of this, there is little stopping Charlatans from pursuing side-matters of interests; equally, afterwards, they can return to grafting anywhere with rich fools willing to part with coin on naught but a promise.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/charlatan.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Halfling, High Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Rogues</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Charlatan Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17