ompendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.9tbHTeuvEMZrp0rx]{Research}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Scholars)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.vMYEkrWj0ip6ZOdv]{Resistance (Disease)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QsrXxGZiHjth7RMg]{Savvy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RWJrupj9seau0w31]{Strike to Injure}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Workshop (Medicine)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.9XJ7Qs6pY6IO01u6]{Court Physician}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Noble)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.OZMvB887CeshFy7b]{Perform (Dancing)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Nobles)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.7bZjB82f6LSkeczP]{Nimble Fingered}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Medicine)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Ywo6fZNPC4zbHHSQ]{Strong-minded}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Courtly Attire, Letter of Appointment<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"Mn7w0SSGfN7cu7gQ","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":5300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Duellist","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘First blood, ye fool! First blood! And here ye’ve gone ‘n run ‘im through!’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>- Ortolf Ehardt, Burgher</em></p><p> ‘In my defense, sir, he was the first to do any sort of bleeding.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>- Rosabel Viernau, Duelist</em></p><p> ‘Always make sure you have Doktor Schuller on site. Deniability? Good question. Pay her in advance, treat her with civility, and she’ll turn around. Ten she sees nothing until the duel is over, one way or another.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>- Blademaster Aleksandr Amblestadt’s advice to his students.</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>Your blade is an instrument of justice, bound by long tradition and employed with deadly precision. </em></p><p>Duelists fight on behalf of others — settling matters of honor between organizations or individuals — or as surrogates for the law, representing the accused or the accuser in trials by combat. For some Duelists the act of fighting is reward enough for the considerable risks they face. Training is dangerous, leaving some apprentices crippled or scarred for life. Those who live long enough to learn from their mistakes can aspire to the fame of a Blademaster, teaching their techniques to eager students. Judicial Champions duel on behalf of governments and nobles, and their blades can determine the fates of nations. Some modern Duelists, especially hot-headed Altdorf students, favor pistols. Tis is regarded by the older generation as dishonorable and fool-hardy.</p><p>Both inexperienced and esteemed Duelists alike travel the Empire in search of opponents with which to bolster their reputations. For others, the hunt for a veteran instructor drives them to explore the furthest ﬂung of the Old World’s locales. Masters of foreign techniques are also sought by Duelists who wish to add unique styles of fighting to their repertoires. As skilled combatants, Duelists often augment their livelihood with mercenary work, even acting as guards for caravans and riverboats in a pinch. Although Dwarfs have no interest in fencing with ﬂimsy swords and the frippery of the dueling scene, they have long traditions of using combat to resolve bitter disputes, and will travel far to enhance their skills.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/duellist.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, High Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Courtier</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Duellist Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.UPATU6CmkbK1mNBe]{Fencer}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.61L9aX2z164cjm7K]{Language (Classical)}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Any)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.L1MoarOIAlia1Ti4]{Beat Blade}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.MoiYSfJRPHu7SZCQ]{Distract}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0pXva9EODy9bngQX]{Feint}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.HpGjzrSR4tdogJtl]{Step Aside}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Hand Weapon or Rapier, Sling Bag containing Clothing and 1d10 Bandages<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.nh8fc9wESGUgOnIh]{Duelist}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bJBesrdCaDqaXbQg]{Melee (Parry)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.H2upcZ7q7qAPtPic]{Ranged (Blackpowder)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Gunsmith)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.tXKX29QZBdHmyMc7]{Combat Reflexes}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5eDd6iFeR9G6cCfz]{Fast Shot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QolNfSUkezLoAcky]{Reversal}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Main Gauche or Sword-breaker, Pistol with Gunpowder and Ammunition<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.DWAc2CYtbwx7zMwl]{Duelmaster}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.vQtJqX0qb0bbpVDg]{Perform (Acrobatics)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IFKWu98qmWpaSfUi]{Ambidextrous}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.DS44h27iCOvUBa4O]{Disarm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x8jsChg17VQ9XgiK]{Riposte}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Rapier, Hand Weapon, Trusty Second, 2 Wooden Training Swords<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.ZRS6U3ECK8n4mFZ4]{Judicial Champion}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.2LDCVJQWkTFszMok]{Lore (Law)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.NDetl9BhAQBVnHKf]{Combat Master}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.4AqSkJnFPqNuTkos]{Reaction Strike}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RWJrupj9seau0w31]{Strike to Injure}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: 2 Quality Weapons<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"3r4A1DOiF3laRWvq","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Smuggler","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘See, this is where the bottle of best Bordeleaux goes. The river wardens will search behind here, and find it, and confiscate it. That’s what we want because it means they don’t find the twelve bottles we have hidden under here. And if they find those, all is not lost, because they will be so pleased with themselves they won’t even bother searching over there where there’s twenty-four bottles.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Hansel Solomon, Smuggler</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>You smuggle cargo, avoiding taxes and risking riverwarden inspections to secure maximum profit.</em></p><p>Most trade is legally taxed by local lords, as well as illegally taxed by bandits and protection rackets. Smugglers see themselves as charitable helpers: merchants make more profit, customers pay less coin, morally ﬂexible Riverwardens take a cut, outlaws are avoided, and more besides. It takes experience and ingenuity to circumvent all the bailiffs, custom officials, excisemen, and busy bodies keen to stop them, but Smugglers dare the risks to support themselves and their family.</p><p>Smugglers come in many forms, perhaps transporting tiny, high-value goods for nobles, or large cargoes for shady merchants. Some Smugglers also deal in illicit goods, a crime that will incur significantly more repercussions than a burned finger or smugglers’ brand.</p><p>Smugglers find adventure, even though they usually want things to stay quiet and uneventful. Any number of things can go wrong on a smuggling mission, and even if things go right, there will always be the lure of the next job, likely bigger and better than the last. Whole adventures can be played out solely on smuggling missions. Similarly, it will be easy for a smuggler to find gainful employment away from their usual work. Someone with a trick up their sleeve, an eye for detail, and a cool head when things get hot is always going to be a desirable companion on dangerous expeditions and adventures.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/smuggler.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Riverfolk</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Smuggler Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17p