gntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.hodHqFNKAmu40ajh]{Swim}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XIcDsaW4D8wScezw]{Accurate Shot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GU1KpgY3MeFIaDaq]{Careful Strike}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.AwUUEwwf2Vt4ksCN]{Sprinter}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Mail Shirt, Riding Horse and Saddle<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.6Abdn6XfJCSI2rWJ]{Bounty Hunter General}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.iYan4z52v7HYM9u9]{Drive}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.2LDCVJQWkTFszMok]{Lore (Law)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jLJzZb4keVvE0qRv]{Deadeye Shot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8pVzgPkgWpTJvfhG]{Fearless (Bounties)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zImcTgEl2XNnbu5W]{Hardy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.phXzaUxl3mFqkmDq]{Sure Shot}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Draught Horse and Cart, Mail Shirt, 4 Pairs of Manacles<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"orZTfdJCm6OnUktl","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Villager","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><p>‘It’s a hard life, for sure, but it’s a good one. Every year the lady from the manor sends out her guard to clear out the forest and drive off the beastmen and the like. The family keep us safe, we keep their ﬂocks. It’s a fair trade most of the time.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Gunni Ackermann, Shepherdess</em></p><p>‘Look, you can sneer at me all you want, but Konrad the Hero his-bloomin’-self was from a village just like mine, so don’t you be talking us down, you hear! Us villagers are good folk!’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"> <em>– Erika Bauer, Farmer</em></p></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>You are the beating heart of rural life, working the countryside to feed civilization.</em></p><p>Sigmar’s bountiful Empire provides an abundant harvest of crops, livestock, and other marketable goods, so there is always plenty of work to be found in the countryside. Villagers make up most of the Empire’s population and perform a variety of valuable roles, including Farmers, Charcoal Burners, Woodsmen, Millers, Herders, and many more. Most villages fall under the domain of a noble family, where the day-to-day administration of the estate is overseen by a bailiff. Village affairs are usually managed by a village council of local tradesmen and farmers led by an Elder. A village Councilor or Elder can hold significant local inﬂuence overseeing many decisions concerning the surrounding land.</p><p>The pastoral safety of a sheltered village is an unspeakable bore for some young Villagers who listen avidly to the tales of faraway lands. Of course, the stories they hear from wandering Pedlars and Strigany, all fueling schemes to escape, bear little relation to the harsh reality of Empire life. During winter, when food is short, and the fields do not need tending, young folk venturing to nearby towns and cities for work often never return, soon caught in the net of civilization’s excitement and adventure.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/villager.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Peasants</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Villager Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.wlH2GnvZKA4zvdn8]{Peasant}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.MXy22hFCgntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.jLyoyqwmBVPjRjhM]{Melee (Brawling)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.FF41XPboORgyDNsv]{Strong Back}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Ywo6fZNPC4zbHHSQ]{Strong-minded}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.spdiWsONKTzkLbg3]{Stone Soup}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: None<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.TvTXvNwAR0hYz0FM]{Villager}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.iYan4z52v7HYM9u9]{Drive}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.qBm2fu3oMhxsDBNQ]{Entertain (Storytelling)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9fq6p9Q6H02LjaSi]{Animal Affinity}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zImcTgEl2XNnbu5W]{Hardy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jviOQmy0luQOySC2]{Tenacious}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Zf0vk2rjllpDh0Ua]{Very Strong}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Leather Jerkin, Hand Weapon (Axe), Trade Tools (as Trade)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.gb3Dy4ZgfB7VfBTM]{Councilor}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GRRN3XAKIpEVCY7z]{Craftsman (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.epPBu7x6BRWp2PHG]{Dealmaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RmY0CUjiFYZ3GEKY]{Very Resilient}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Mule and Cart, Village Home and Workshop<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.3UCjABRxB1GhbThg]{Village Elder}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.FChdV10BCuXQyUhU]{Lore (History)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GHmXS9zGNx3PWYZc]{Master Tradesman (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.7bZjB82f6LSkeczP]{Nimble Fingered}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XU7D9CCmumuhqDUi]{Public Speaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Local)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: The Respect of the Village<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"EYkvtokq0FXlFaPa","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":7600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Engineer","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><p>‘What will it do? Well, it’s supposed to pluck the chicken, Smallnose. Stand well back!’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Wolfgang Kugelschrieber, Inventor</em> </p><p>‘Master Engineer Volker von Meinkopt found inspiration watching students reloading at the Imperial Gunnery School. He had a revelation: more barrels = more shots = more lethality. He soon produced the first repeating handgun, ‘Von Meinkopt’s Whirling Cavalcade of Death’, and pistol, ‘Von Meinkopt’s Micro-mainspring of Multitudinous Precipitation of Pernicious Lead’. Not content to rest on those laurels, he then created the enormous nine-barreled cannon, the Helblaster Volley Gun, which is utterly lethal to enemies and, all too often, its crew.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– ‘Great Engineers of the Empire’, Lady Teodora Holzenauer, Engineer and Journalist</em></p></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>You create machines and constructions both useful and bizarre, and often downright deadly.</em></p><p>Engineers design and build mechanical devices or structures such as bridges, canals, or fortifications. Most are educated, Dwarfs at the hide-bound Dwarf Engineers Guild, Humans at forward-thinking establishments such as the Imperial Engineers School at Altdorf, though self-taught prodigies are not unknown. Human Engineers value innovation and discovery, whereas Dwarfs favor traditional, tried-and-tested designs passed down for generations. Mining company engineers are well-paid; less so the State Army Engineers who maintain the Imperial war machines and act as sappers and bridge-builders. Master Engineers often find themselves leading teams on ambitious construction projects. Chartered Engineers are the most trusted in the Empire, called upon to design, test, and build such prestigious Imperial Commissions like the complex Steam Wheel Locks, which have revolutionized the speed of travel in the canals of the Vorbergland.</p><p>Some Engineers are drawn to investigate ancient Dwarf Holds, most now abandoned, for entombed within are the secrets of the master builders of old. Those who dare their depths may find millennia-old marvels, many of which are repurposed by Goblins and Skaven for their own nefarious purposes. Equally enticing are the stone sky bridges soaring above the Holds, some stretching for many miles, true wonders of bygone engineering that once connected thriving Dwarf settlements, forts, and farmlands.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/engineer.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Engineer Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style