♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.zmC4qBprmNxFNo2W]{Scholar}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.fdq3RFSOKl5b3WzW]{Art (Writing)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zv3IyoU2wkPZu8pD]{Bookish}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Scholars)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.kQbVFzsh4LbaIzHU]{Speedreader}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LPgjE0cexTVOBVCY]{Suave}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Access to a Library, Degree<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.txoNWW53klRbo49P]{Fellow}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Lecture)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.726gbrANZt8OqXr5]{Linguistics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XU7D9CCmumuhqDUi]{Public Speaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.V9N0LMnXf1WYseCL]{Tower of Memories}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Mortarboard, Robes<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.IeHydxYWUYrmEdPy]{Professor}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Rhetoric)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QdvY9hoDTbr12jXq]{Magnum Opus}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.ZWcTbeK8i9vKph2a]{Master Orator}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.oQzTJEXUx28sCiH3]{Sharp}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Study<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"CmiCNv8YlslFqRqy","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":6300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Spy","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘Treason? That’s it? For the love of... why didn’t I qualify for high treason? I’ve done plenty of other terrible things. Should I list them off for you? What’s that? It’s not personal? Well, it is now, you prig-powdered gaff ’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Sieben Dietmund, Accused of Treason and Contempt</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>You are the eyes and ears of another, exposing secrets and spreading lies.</em></p><p>Spies are brave (or foolhardy) individuals who secretly gather information for their clients. A well-placed Spy is an asset to anyone desiring knowledge of an opponent’s activities. Many take months, even years, cultivating an unremarkable identity with ties to one or more groups or individuals. Their actions are risky. If caught, Spies are rarely executed quickly and often tortured at length. Many Informers are forced into spying via blackmail or other threats. A skilled Spy will earn well, but extrication from such activities can be more perilous than the activities themselves. Given Spies avoid undue attention, they aren’t typically known by their reputations unless those reputations are as anonymous as they are.</p><p>Spies are found throughout the Old World and in service to many prominent organizations. During their investigations, Spies are easily embroiled in plots both sinister and benign. They are often forced to ﬂee when their identities or allegiances are exposed. These individuals use their abilities to disguise their true nature and avoid capture. Joining a group of unwitting heroes under false pretenses as part of an escape attempt has led more than one Spy to an adventuring career.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/spy.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf, Wood Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Courtier</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Spy Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=