D[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.VscjNv6RzHFb9CQp]{Enclosed Fighter}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8oWhzlcw7oiHGMFu]{Unshakable}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Symbol of Rank, Unit of Troops<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.RjhqM27l48WfRepK]{Officer}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XU7D9CCmumuhqDUi]{Public Speaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jQmIu8P85tF0njmD]{Seasoned Traveller}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Letter of Commission, Light Warhorse with Saddle and Tack, Map, Orders, Unit of Soldiers, Quality Uniform, Symbol of Rank<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"1OTZ386bMWJ6wfzX","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":7100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Stevedore","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘Look, I know we specialize in coal, but don’t fence us in, we’ll port anything if the coin’s good. So, let’s do it afore the deal porters arrive; anything goes here, mate.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Albert Pförtner, Coal Porter</em></p><p> </p><p>‘Listen, boy. Don’t think them dockers have it easy. It’s dangerous, claustrophobic work, with heavy goods and high stacks, and if it’s done wrong, the cargo may overbalance, perhaps even capsizing the boat. What I’m saying is, pay the Stevedores right — and if you want a boat to sink, pay them extra.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Aleida Fuchs, Merchant</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>You may officially load cargo for coin, but everyone knows the Stevedores rule the docklands.</em></p><p>With their sole right to load and unload vessels, Stevedore Guilds can slow or even stop trade. Tis grants power, with many docksides effectively ruled by the guilds. In larger towns, several gangs might violently compete for supremacy. Scowling Foremen deal with guild matters and blow their whistles to summon their gangs from riverside inns, either for fresh work or to defend their territory.</p><p>A Stevedore might work alone in a riverside village, or in a large gang on a busy, chaotic city dockside. Sometimes they might be part of a criminal gang that just moves a bit of cargo on the side to cover their tracks. Some Stevedores are enforcers, making sure everyone else is working hard.</p><p>A Stevedore might work alone in a riverside village, or in a large gang on a busy, chaotic city dockside. Sometimes they might be part of a criminal gang that just moves a bit of cargo on the side to cover their tracks. Some Stevedores are enforcers, making sure everyone else is working hard.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/stevedore.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Riverfolk</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Stevedore Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.p2PKXr5CDwln9AWS]{Dockhand}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.hodHqFNKAmu40ajh]{Swim}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.2Nzqsc9aclP6rpnl]{Dirty Fighting}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.FF41XPboORgyDNsv]{Strong Back}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.qZ4cFy6z482ZONuA]{Sturdy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Zf0vk2rjllpDh0Ua]{Very Strong}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Hand Weapon (Boat Hook), Leather Gloves<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.oce4kxrsImFS7zlW]{Stevedore}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.qBm2fu3oMhxsDBNQ]{Entertain (Storytelling)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zkI6tIqbyAZvh0Th]{Stealth (Urban)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.r180vP86SlwyJc8W]{Criminal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Guilders)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.CV9btQn09S9Fn8Jk]{Strong Legs}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jviOQmy0luQOySC2]{Tenacious}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Guild License, Leather Jerkin, Pipe and Tobacco, Porter Cap<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.CJDvhhZbQ0UxxZKc]{Foreman}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.epPBu7x6BRWp2PHG]{Dealmaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.HIofcsDLjXGKzSZf]{Embezzle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Criminals)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XU7D9CCmumuhqDUi]{Public Speaker}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Gang of Stevedores, Whistle<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.9PTQfMr98E3ei3Fo]{Dock Master}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Taxes)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RbnrfHf7GSQap0ig]{Kingpin}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5QcrpLQWWrsbKR79]{Numismatics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Office and Sta?, Writing Kit<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"KslqDlYmY4trmf6S","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":7300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Miner","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>After your supplies from the store are deducted, and your load of sixteen tons added, you made…let me see… no, you actually owe us two for today. Another day older and deeper in debt, boy.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Frederika, Victualler of the Delfgruber Minehead</em>.</p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><div><p><em>A hewer of stone, you pursue back-breaking work in the darkest depths of the world.</em></p><p>Many prospectors are tempted by stories of gold in the Skaag Hills, but real mining is hard work down dark, dangerous tunnels. Adept at constructing supports and assessing mineral ores for their value, Miners are alert to unexpected dangers from explosive gas to tunneling Greenskins, and are notoriously tough, both physically and mentally. Prospectors usually work on commission, with a license to prospect in return for sharing finds with the local lord. Some noble houses’ fortunes are built on the rich mines in their lands, and often Miners in these pits will be criminals or debtors pressed into service. Quarrymen hewing open-face stone ostensibly have a safer job than those underground, but accidents are common and Beastman attack from the forest is an ever-present danger.</p><p>Many independent Miners find themselves thrust into peril when set upon by Goblins or other subterranean horrors. Some find the rewards of this life more lucrative, if not less dangerous, than slaving away for a mine owner for a pittance. Prospectors have many opportunities for adventure and can easily pull together a band of like-minded folk eager for riches and glory.</p><p>To Dwarfs, mining is not an occupation limited to commoners. Rather, they are considered artisans of great skill and are well-respected amongst the Dawi. Possessed of a keen sense for stone, Dwarfs are drawn to valuable seams and seemingly have a sixth-sense for when to shore up passages. Some Dwarf clans hold such pride in their mining ability that they march to war armed with picks rather than axes.</p></div></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/miner.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Peasants</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Miner Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.tJEgkiklMFep6FMN]{Prospector}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Two-handed)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.hodHqFNKAmu40ajh]{Swim}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1dUizIgLBgn4jICC]{Strider (Rocky)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.qZ4cFy6z482ZONuA]{Sturdy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jviOQmy0luQOySC2]{Tenacious}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Charcoal Stick, Crude Map, Pan, Spade<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.oVOBKzVocBrnrpZX]{Miner}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bVdhLdfuSAfMi3qq]{Secret Signs (Miner)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Explosives)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x0WMGwuQzReXcQrs]{Night Vision}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.4MJJCiOKPkBByYwW]{Strike Mighty Blow}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.FF41XPboORgyDNsv]{Strong Back}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Zf0vk2rjllpDh0Ua]{Very Strong}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Davrich Lamp, Hand Weapon (Pick), Lamp Oil, Leather Jack<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.hUZ9lx9v2AGrfHWU]{Master Miner}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.VNjHDKWD6sIbF6BI]{Lore (Geology)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cHbQeJQ7cVZZyDyl]{Stealth (Underground)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Engineer)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GU1KpgY3MeFIaDaq]{Careful Strike}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GRRN3XAKIpEVCY7z]{Craftsman (Explosives)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6lQRRgjz8IZH4bbV]{Tinker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Z91GFaT6FhEwyESU]{Tunnel Rat}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Great Weapon (Two-handed Pick), Helmet, Trade Tools (Engineer)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.3qe5qu3es4bnKwwR]{Mine Foreman}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.41JhsSNW1Ttza3JK]{Argumentative}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Ywo6fZNPC4zbHHSQ]{Strong-minded}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.HIofcsDLjXGKzSZf]{Embezzle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Crew of Miners, Writing Kit<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"Nu2diwbUfo786wYt","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":4600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Fence","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><p>‘I know it’s stolen. You know it’s stolen. Even old Sigmar knows it’s stolen. So when I ask you if it’s stolen, don’t insult me by telling me it isn’t stolen. Lucky for you, I deal in stolen, so stop panicking.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Elene Weslach, Mover</em></p><p> ‘Why am I called a Fence? Well, it’s because I provide you with some de-fence from being caught, innit. So, you go thief, and I’ll make sure you don’t have to worry about how to shift the merchandise. Think of me like your partner-in-crime.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– ‘Boil’ Vakram, Fence</em></p></div></div></blockquote><div style=\"direction:ltr;border-width:100%\"><div style=\"direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in\"><div style=\"direction:ltr;margin-top:0in;margin-left:0in;width:6.6041in\"><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt;text-align:right\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\"> </span></p><p><em>A shrewd assessor of valuables, you’ll buy anything, legal or not, and turn it around for a tidy profit.</em></p><p>A Fence buys thieves’ spoils and sells it on for profit, often to those unaware the goods are stolen. Successful Fences sometimes operate as pawn brokers, importers, or other merchants. Others prefer to remain mobile, trafficking only in portable items. Though the average Fence deals in goods and valuables, there are also well-informed specialists who focus on information and forbidden knowledge. Some Fences move stolen items across the Empire. A painting stolen in Altdorf is easier to sell in Talabheim to an audience unaware of the theft. When high profile items vanish, Fences are also the first individuals to be consulted by those looking to acquire them. Some Fences even take commissions from clients, connecting them with those who can steal to order.</p><p>The search for buyers and sellers, or the need to escape a terrible situation, can take a Fence anywhere. They can be found across the Empire and in many regions beyond its borders. Up-and-coming Brokers transport illicit goods between Old World cities in search of buyers. Others, looking to make a name for themselves elsewhere, attempt to make their own niches in existing city underworlds. Given that their interests often collide, Fences and merchants make occasional bedfellows, as well. With all of this criminal activity and movement, trouble often follows</p><p style=\"margin:0in;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\"> </span></p></div></div></div><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/fence.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Rogues</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Fence Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.7w3Y5lZXMBa7N0uV]{Broker}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.wBhPFggGqIXwbx1r]{Alley Cat}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Yiw5h1Kj4B2WLlfm]{Cardsharp}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.epPBu7x6BRWp2PHG]{Dealmaker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8lSoPDGrmeTIaapm]{Gregarious}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Hand Weapon, Stolen Goods worth 3d10 Shillings<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.uNG01MDCaG4zcs6U]{Fence}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bVdhLdfuSAfMi3qq]{Secret Signs (Thief )}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Engraver)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.r180vP86SlwyJc8W]{Criminal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Criminals)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5QcrpLQWWrsbKR79]{Numismatics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QsrXxGZiHjth7RMg]{Savvy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Eye-glass, Trade Tools (Engraver), Writing Kit<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.HN1cbMIPZ25m7ABR]{Master Fence}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.qBm2fu3oMhxsDBNQ]{Entertain (Storytelling)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Art)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RbnrfHf7GSQap0ig]{Kingpin}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jt0DmVK9IiF6Sd2h]{Strike to Stun}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LPgjE0cexTVOBVCY]{Suave}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sBHarYXR2o7jD1VY]{Super Numerate}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Pawnbroker's Shop<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.bO6PkXjLPKCwK4QC]{Black Marketeer}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DiP9cmbqUir3HkkK]{Lore (Heraldry)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.9tbHTeuvEMZrp0rx]{Research}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.2Nzqsc9aclP6rpnl]{Dirty Fighting}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.34EBUkHQkrqF1sq7]{Briber}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Hired Muscle, Network of Informants, Warehouse<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"VzMDRJtha7epNzuX","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Wizard","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘I don’t care what promises they make, or what colleges they belong to, they are dangerous abominations. I am continuing to petition for their destruction in the name of Sigmar, for the good of us all.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– ‘Reikhardt Mair, Witch Hunter</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p> </p><div><div><div><p><em>Feared and distrusted by the citizens of the Empire, you legally wield powerful and dangerous magic. </em></p><p>Wizards channel one of the eight ‘Winds of Magic’ only spellcasters perceive, to cast potent spells. To legally cast magic in the Empire, a Human must follow the Articles of Imperial Magic and belong to one of the Eight Colleges of Magic in Altdorf — each dedicated to a specific wind, as Magisters can only safely channel one. After graduation, Apprentices become Magisters and serve the Empire. Magisters carefully study and practice their art, which, according to the Articles, they can only use outside their colleges in defense of their own life, or against the enemies of the Empire. Many Magisters are attached to the Empire State Army, and although they are treated with cautious suspicion, none can deny their effectiveness on the battlefield.</p><p>Many Magisters leave the Colleges of Magic in debt for the cost of their tuition. These Wizards may be keen to find immediate employment, or seek out their fortune on land, at sea, or anywhere else they might be able to find relics, artefacts or lost tomes of magical lore. Journeying Magisters, eager to prove themselves, are actively encouraged to test their skills across the Empire by hunting down whatever dangers threaten the local populace.</p><p>Wizards are excellent characters to add some firepower to a group, but it can be intimidating for new players to have to learn a whole additional set of rules for spells. Because of this the GM should be aware that they might initially need some extra support to ensure that they are using these rules effectively and to the group’s best advantage. You’ll choose the color of magic you study when you take the Arcane Magic Talent. For more on magic see Chapter 8: Magic.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/wizard.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, High Elf, Wood Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Wizard Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.WiMLDa950d9wsbbZ]{Wizard's Apprentice}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling (Any Color)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Grimoire, Staff<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.JeWuOwm0nM4V1brh]{Wizard}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Battle)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Any Arcane Lore)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.g3y373FnWJEAxgEB]{Detect Artefact}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9sMAf0xmehjEmUao]{Fast Hands}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Magical License<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.1DIMUn1Cj5rohWJV]{Master Wizard}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.MXy22hFCgntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BYChSVfMG004eflQ]{Instinctive Diction}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Light Warhorse, Magical Item<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.bTPBxrayfzeVmGsh]{Wizard Lord}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.F2EiuAc6IpaGd4J7]{War Wizard}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Library (Magic), Workshop (Magic)<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"PKm1L6yjZ4PH0JJG","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":8200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Outlaw","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘They were children, not brigands. Starving, filthy, sickly. They held us under the sight of their arrows and we stood fast… my son’s age, they were. Children. Killed six of us…’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Valentin Behr, Roadwarden</em></p><p> ‘...and he says, “Titus, why d’you carry them shears?” And I says, “These?” And he says, “Aye, those’re the only shears I see.” So I laughed and answered: “Sometimes they don’t want to take off their rings like I ask ‘em to. When I show ‘em the shears, most of ‘em change their tune right quick. And if they don’t…’’. Hehehe.’ </p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Hasslich Widmann, Outlaw</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p><em>You prey upon travelers, extracting a toll from the vulnerable and the unsuspecting.</em></p><p>Outlaws ply the roads of the Old World in search of vulnerable travelers and merchant caravans. They lead dangerous and often hardscrabble lives. Many do not see themselves as criminals, but as oppressed groups trying to live their lives free from outside constraints. Many Wood Elf outlaws ft this description, pushing back against the Humans proliferating at the edge of the forests, willing to take more drastic action than others of their kind. Particularly savvy and brutal Outlaws may form bands of their own, sometimes even uniting several bands under a single banner. Such Bandit Kings are feared and reviled by noble and peasant alike. Tough few Outlaws discriminate in choosing their prey, some claim to protect the common man. These do-gooders focus their larceny on greedy nobles and, in return, locals may provide them with food, information, and safe harbor.</p><p>Outlaw bands are not all wild mobs, so many can be reasoned with if approached correctly. An Outlaw might be asked to accompany a group of adventurers as a guide or to protect them, especially if the group are trying to stop unholy activity in a Bandit King’s domain. Individual Outlaws may find it simple to join an adventuring band, although they may need to disguise themselves if they go anywhere the Outlaw is wanted.</p><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/outlaw.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf, Wood Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Rogues</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Outlaw Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.0e98xv2tfsDRZ9kU]{Brigand}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.r180vP86SlwyJc8W]{Criminal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jrFIFLhyOYwcyMUl]{Flee!}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Bedroll, Hand Weapon, Leather Jerkin, Tinderbox<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.9631KpCQa7jvhmgS]{Outlaw}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.ZQSm2AwrgT2cHG0C]{Ranged (Bow)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Xk5tp3aasPNtk4zt]{Stealth (Rural)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.2Nzqsc9aclP6rpnl]{Dirty Fighting}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5lcttqGToT54WFrl]{Marksman}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jt0DmVK9IiF6Sd2h]{Strike to Stun}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.a7v422EZcOUUC20X]{Trapper}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Bow with 10 Arrows, Shield, Tent<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.qXOceBlJefsWFlUI]{Outlaw Chief}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.769B469sqx6FXPfn]{Rapid Reload}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9CAkY3SQjQxRTlNJ]{Roughrider}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RmY0CUjiFYZ3GEKY]{Very Resilient}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Helmet, Riding Horse with Saddle and Tack, Sleeved Mail Shirt, Band of Outlaws<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.g2vYtD3Mu7ujYTVF]{Bandit King}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Empire)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jLJzZb4keVvE0qRv]{Deadeye Shot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8pVzgPkgWpTJvfhG]{Fearless (Road Wardens)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.nWLsoWQBCjPRKxYx]{Robust}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: 'Fiefdom' of Outlaw Chiefs, Lair<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"SrqxyWytyki4WYgC","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":5100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Protagonist","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><p>‘Remember Tommy Two Knives? I’m not saying he crossed me. I’m just saying you don’t see him walking round town no more, do you?’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Gilly Tree Knives, Protagonist</em></p><p>‘Yeah, Big Yuri came round and destroyed all my merchandise. Said this town was only big enough for one lotus dealer, and that was that. I completely agreed, so I doubled his pay and sent him back to White Tiger’s den. And that was the end of that.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Toni Miragliano, Lotus Dealer</em></p></div></div></blockquote><p><em>A strong-arm for hire, you bully, fight, and maybe even kill for coin.</em></p><div><div><div><p>Protagonists live by their wits and their muscles and are not generally fussy about the sort of work they take on. A merchant might want to frighten their business rival. An employer might decide his workers need a bit of encouragement to get a job done quicker. A noble might want his daughter’s no-good suitor to be frightened off. Protagonists are the ones they turn to, and those with the worst reputation get the best jobs. A Protagonist could be the brute in the local bar everyone knows will bully for coin, or with the reputation for unﬂinching violence. Some Protagonists have their own code of what they will or won’t do; others care for nothing but the coin. Some are simple bullies who resort to picking arguments and fights with likely looking targets to see if they can score any money from the situation.</p><p>On the face of it, Protagonists are always up for an adventure because they’re always up for a fight. But they will usually expect to get paid for services rendered. Whether they will join others without a guarantee of payment is a question they will need to ask themselves. Could a hardened protagonist find a cause they will voluntarily pursue? Perhaps they could even turn over a new leaf?</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/protagonist.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, High Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Warrior</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Protagonist Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.qMZiB9eBUEr7omX0]{Braggart}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Taunt)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Any)}</em><br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.tX9R9rSYm2YyEnOK]{In-fighter}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.2Nzqsc9aclP6rpnl]{Dirty Fighting}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zGQ0ShUTSlUvVtWh]{Warrior Born}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Hood or Mask, Knuckledusters, Leather Jack<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.ZydFv9TTPvmihnR1]{Protagonist}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.d3VZwO4Y5JH5DXdT]{Bribery}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.tXKX29QZBdHmyMc7]{Combat Reflexes}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.r180vP86SlwyJc8W]{Criminal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QolNfSUkezLoAcky]{Reversal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jt0DmVK9IiF6Sd2h]{Strike to Stun}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Hand Weapon, Mail Shirt, Riding Horse with Saddle and Tack, Shield<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.33COmPgYTVuXXIpK]{Hitman}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.NSnpJQiky8JcMnme]{Ranged (Throwing)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GU1KpgY3MeFIaDaq]{Careful Strike}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.DS44h27iCOvUBa4O]{Disarm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5lcttqGToT54WFrl]{Marksman}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.SgjJMBgc85aswvhm]{Relentless}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Cloak, Garotte, Poison, Throwing Knives<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.HtN6uHPj7sK6EWMZ]{Assassin}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Acting)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.OuDdJRDo3W56zk0Z]{Ranged (Crossbow)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XIcDsaW4D8wScezw]{Accurate Shot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IFKWu98qmWpaSfUi]{Ambidextrous}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BlHVzfs0Ow6IYEDw]{Furious Assault}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RWJrupj9seau0w31]{Strike to Injure}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Crossbow with 10 shots, Disguise Kit<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"cXOl6phkTrPcUmwC","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":5700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Knight","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><p>‘The knight demanded I get out of his way. “Why?” I asked. “I am in the service of the people,” he replied. “Well, I’m the people,” I said, “so I don’t have to get out of your way.” He didn’t have an answer to that, of course. So he punched me in the face!’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Holger Kass, 1st Bögenhafen Halberdiers</em></p><p> ‘Lady Myrmaelia Jaeke is the finest knight in the Order of the Blazing Sun. How can I be so sure? Well, I used to hold that title, and she bested me.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Birgitte van der Hoogenband, Abbess-General of the Monastery of the Black Maiden, former Knight of the Blazing Sun.</em></p></div></div></blockquote><p><em>Thundering into battle on a heavy charger, you dominate the field, spreading fear in your wake.</em></p><div><div><div><p>Many believe heavy cavalry are the pre-eminent warriors of the Old World. A massed charge is an awesome sight, but even alone a Knight can stand as a one-person army. There are many Knightly Orders in the Empire, the most famous including the Reiksguard, the White Wolves, the Knights Panther, and the Knights Griffon, each of which have their own gloried history and mighty heroes. Most Empire Knights belong to secular knightly orders, partly because training heavy lancers is too prohibitively expensive for most nobles. The templar orders, those dedicated to the service of a single deity are just as common but are somewhat more independent. Alongside these are an uncounted number of free-lances, mercenary knights, and disgraced knights, most of whom sell their lance to the highest bidder.</p><p>Knights might be asked to venture out to fulfill a duty on behalf of their Order or be sought out by nobles and employed to accompany a restless heir around the Empire. Similarly, templars will have responsibility to do their god’s will. All of these provide perfect opportunities for Knights looking to adventure. By comparison, a free-lance is just that, and a life of adventure is what they follow by default.</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/knight.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, High Elf, Wood Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Warrior</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Knight Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.FrPCbQ7fq1Fchthn]{Squire}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.MXy22hFCgntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.4IGdIhnwTaZijzg7]{Charm Animal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DiP9cmbqUir3HkkK]{Lore (Heraldry)}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rt1yfcjZoeSulddW]{Melee (Cavalry)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Farrier)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9CAkY3SQjQxRTlNJ]{Roughrider}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.qZ4cFy6z482ZONuA]{Sturdy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zGQ0ShUTSlUvVtWh]{Warrior Born}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Leather Jack, Mail Shirt, Riding Horse with Saddle and Tack, Shield, Trade Tools (Farrier)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.FhK6JOd3LSTlHwoa]{Knight}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Battle)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jQmIu8P85tF0njmD]{Seasoned Traveller}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IT3s7rmQFGNzIfYq]{Shieldsman}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.4MJJCiOKPkBByYwW]{Strike Mighty Blow}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Destrier with Saddle and Tack, Melee Weapon (Any), Lance, Plate Armor and Helm<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.GPhqluMBhCeTnyNJ]{First Knight}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8pVzgPkgWpTJvfhG]{Fearless (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8oWhzlcw7oiHGMFu]{Unshakable}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Barding, Small Unit of Knights<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.Esy17RVOZQw2gShT]{Knight of the Inner Circle}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bVdhLdfuSAfMi3qq]{Secret Signs (Knightly Order)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.DS44h27iCOvUBa4O]{Disarm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RWJrupj9seau0w31]{Strike to Injure}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Plumed Great Helm, Squire, Large Unit of Knights or Several Small Units of Knights<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"L3YNSsFKnqrqcmTn","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":4000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Hedge Witch","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘We tell the folk that the offering o’ fish is for Grandfather Reik, ‘cause it makes them feel safer than having to explain the river is home to an ‘ungry spirit. It keeps the spirit safe, too.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Alt Zaunreiter, Hedgewise</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p><em>Wise and secretive, you guide your community using ancient magic handed down for generations.</em></p><div><div><div><p>Witch Hunters use the term ‘Hedge Witch’ for any illegal spellcaster, but this was not always so. Once Hedge Witches were respected members of rural communities, practicing magics older than the forests. But decades of persecution since the founding of the Colleges of Magic have left the few surviving Hedge Witches disparate and broken. They hide in the quietest corners of the Old World, their smoky huts and creaking hovels standing astride the boundary between civilization and the trackless wilds. Most Hedge Witches are solitary to protect themselves from prying strangers, but their talents are often known to locals. Their knowledge of warding evil is usually secret, but their herbalism, midwifery, and healing arts are quickly sought in times of need</p><p>A Hedge Witch is often the first to notice supernatural foul play. The subsequent investigations often lead to all sorts of dangers and adventure. When Witch Hunters come to town, Hedge Witches often take a leave of absence, lying low or travelling elsewhere until danger is passed.</p><p>The Hedgefolk are known by many names across the Empire, but have one thing in common: the goal of preserving their ancient traditions from destruction. Hedge Witches have little love for the Colleges of Magic, knowing any child taken by them will likely never return to serve their community, instead pressed into service in some far-off war. Whenever possible they hide children they consider ‘blessed’ from passing magisters, although occasionally one will be sent to the Colleges — as a sacrifice or a spy, who can say?</p></div></div></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/hedge-witch.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Peasants</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\">Hedge Witch Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.QreTSlhgK9IfwTJa]{Hedge Apprentice}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.V8eRx66SxB9Jha0Q]{Channelling}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Folklore)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Herbs)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9sMAf0xmehjEmUao]{Fast Hands}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1dUizIgLBgn4jICC]{Strider (Woodlands)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: 1d10 Lucky Charms, Quarterstaff, Backpack<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.7LERztK8LMIMwo4l]{Hedge Witch}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Local)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Charms)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Herbalist)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9fq6p9Q6H02LjaSi]{Animal Affinity}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Hedgecraft)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Antitoxin Kit, Healing Poultice, Trade Tools (Herbalist)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.MvMAvys9IhMIgNqX]{Hedge Master}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Genealogy)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Spirits)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GRRN3XAKIpEVCY7z]{Craftsman (Herbalist)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.wNvPXAhlKABl6hpk]{Pure Soul}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.vMYEkrWj0ip6ZOdv]{Resistance (Disease)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Isolated Hut, Apprentice<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.fa7YavtVsSc8QI7Q]{Hedgewise}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.9xR9uO8FIvi4YsJp]{Pray}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9h82z72XGo9tfgQS]{Acute Sense (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GHmXS9zGNx3PWYZc]{Master Tradesman (Herbalist)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x0WMGwuQzReXcQrs]{Night Vision}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.Ywo6fZNPC4zbHHSQ]{Strong-minded}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Assortment of Animal Skulls, Ceremonial Cloak and Garland<br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"_id":"03Nnub5GHNRCU9kg","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":3500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Guard","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><p>‘I stood outside the shrine for thirty days and thirty nights, without fail. No one got in and no one got out. Of course, it turned out I was stood outside the wrong door.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Ernst Bluchard, Ex-Temple Guard of Manann</em></p><p>‘If you’re not on the list, you’re not coming in!’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Anonymous Altdorf guard to the Grand Theogonist at the coronation of Karl-Franz I, apocryphal</em></p></blockquote><p><em>Your job is simple: keep undesirables out</em></p><div><p>The best way to keep something safe is to post a guard. Guarding looks easy enough, it’s usually standing around doing very little. Guards live and die, quite literally, by how they behave during that one moment when they are required to spring into action. The best can command high wages and are entrusted with the lives of the Empire’s finest personages and most valuable items. Guards are everywhere from the Imperial palace, down to bouncers who might stand outside a tavern all night and throw drunks into the street. Grave wardens fending off grave robbers from Morr’s Gardens. Temple guards defend temples and important priests. Merchants often require guards locally, for valuable cargo stored in a warehouse or in transit. Some claim personal bodyguards have the most interesting guarding jobs because they must stay with their esteemed employers, and they get to see important lives going on first hand.</p><p>Guards can find adventure when their guardianship is compromised. Any guard worth his salt would wish to follow up and investigate those who have thwarted them, and get whatever they were guarding back to its true owner. This could easily turn into an exciting adventure. Many of those going on expeditions will require guards to accompany them, to adventure, profit or an untimely demise.</p></div><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/guard.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf, Wood Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Warrior</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Guard Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.gTxHixydLdCoWRmj]{Sentry}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.qBm2fu3oMhxsDBNQ]{Entertain (Storytelling)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}</em><br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.cAxNctMFWIAjDgV3]{Diceman}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Servants)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jt0DmVK9IiF6Sd2h]{Strike to Stun}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jviOQmy0luQOySC2]{Tenacious}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Buckler, Leather Jerkin, Storm Lantern with Oil<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.9q1yLMpfhX1bqvth]{Guard}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.ZQSm2AwrgT2cHG0C]{Ranged (Bow)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.SgjJMBgc85aswvhm]{Relentless}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QolNfSUkezLoAcky]{Reversal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IT3s7rmQFGNzIfYq]{Shieldsman}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.4MJJCiOKPkBByYwW]{Strike Mighty Blow}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Bow with 10 Arrows, Sleeved Mail Shirt, Shield, Spear<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.pUf4a817P7iydsbN]{Honour Guard}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Battle)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Etiquette)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Two-handed)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8pVzgPkgWpTJvfhG]{Fearless (Intruders)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BIaLeh4CPFaTMbFz]{Jump Up}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8oWhzlcw7oiHGMFu]{Unshakable}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Great Weapon or Halberd, Helmet, Uniform<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.careers.rAfHb0jmWhNfXaBl]{Guard Officer}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.NDetl9BhAQBVnHKf]{Combat Master}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BlHVzfs0Ow6IYEDw]{Furious Assault}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.nWLsoWQBCjPRKxYx]{Robust}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Breastplate</p>","markdown":""},"_id":"HndWncfaHb0nzNUq","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":3200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}}},{"name":"Artist","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<blockquote><div><div><div><p>‘Please remain still, my lord. It is rather difficult to capture the majesty of your countenance if you continue to scratch yourself so. Perfect! Now hold that pose for just a few seconds more if you please. And there you’ve gone and done it again. Might I suggest you pay a visit to the apothecary? He may have several effective remedies for lice, especially if you find your incessant squirming as bothersome as I do...’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"> <em>– Gottlieb Toman, Painter, prior to his execution</em></p></div></div></div></blockquote><p><em>You possess an artistic gift, one that transcends daily life and uplifts the souls of others</em></p><p>Artists use their talents — for painting, sculpting, writing and similar — to create works of fine art. Often their careers begin as Apprentices to experienced Master Artists, though some are simply prodigies. The best can attract a patron, and some end up teaching, forming their own schools of art and attracting the wealthiest of benefactors to their fashionable salons.</p><p>Sadly, most Artists spend their lives in a vain attempt to prove their value to a society that rarely appreciates them. Some make ends meet through different means: satirizing nobles and politicians in cartoons for the Altdorf broadsheets, sketching suspects for watch captains, writing social commentary, or even forging the work of more renowned artists</p><p>Attracting suitable patrons is not always a simple matter, so Artists of all stripes find themselves traveling abroad in search of one. Even those who have the means to support themselves take to the road in search of new sights to paint, sculpt, or inspire them. Holy frescos and reliefs dedicated to the gods are often commissioned in faraway temples, churches, and abbeys.</p><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/artist.webp\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human, Dwarf, Halfling, High Elf, Wood Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Courtier</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Artist Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr