Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.fEFAMNqh8nJIfBkM]{Field Dressing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.nWLsoWQBCjPRKxYx]{Robust}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Plate Breastplate, Sash of Rank<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-up-in-arms.items.gCnCMl8nQVDdgsFj]{Banner Captain}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.2LDCVJQWkTFszMok]{Lore (Law)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8oWhzlcw7oiHGMFu]{Unshakable}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.RmY0CUjiFYZ3GEKY]{Very Resilient}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Baton of Rank, Banner-Bearer, Light Warhorse, Quality Uniform, Plate Bracers and Leggings, Phalanx of Pikemen, Unit Banner <br /><br /></p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"_id":"mGMZSWoJnbnRze1h","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":5400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.h7yDZkJj94QMA46z.JournalEntryPage.mGMZSWoJnbnRze1h"}}},{"name":"Freelance","text":{"content":"<p><em>You pursue the life of the knight, but without the obligations to, or the protection of, a Knightly Order.</em></p><p>Not all knights belong to an order, there are those who are knighted independently by a noble, others declare themselves a knight, and there are some who leave (or are thrown out…) of an Order to forge their own path. These are known as ‘freelancers’, knights who fight for coin, honour, or some peculiar motive of their own.  Some are hardened mercenaries or little better than bandits. Others are champions of the downtrodden or selfless unsung heroes of the people.</p><p>Freelancers are as diverse as their origins. They wear their own colours, which may be a family crest if they are noble or heraldry of their own devising. Eccentric arms and armour are common, assembled from their own preferences or whatever they can obtain and maintain. They are often viewed with suspicion, as they have no Order to vouch for their disposition, but if their actions are heroic, they can become popular.  Advancement outside an order is unstructured — typically a freelancer grows their retinue and eventually leads their own troop of knights. An example of this is Voland’s Venators, a notoriously rowdy band of knights who fight as mercenaries in Tilea, the Border Princes, and the Empire.</p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-up-in-arms/assets/actors/freelance.webp\" width=\"435\" height=\"747\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Warrior</p><h3 class=\"no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Freelance Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-up-in-arms.items.TLx7hxFsMrlI5cUs]{Squire}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.LGHozP5gmQ8cuDQV]{Athletics}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.MXy22hFCgntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.4IGdIhnwTaZijzg7]{Charm Animal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.HXZaV1CJhmTvcAz4]{Heal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rt1yfcjZoeSulddW]{Melee (Cavalry)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Farrier)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9CAkY3SQjQxRTlNJ]{Roughrider}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.qZ4cFy6z482ZONuA]{Sturdy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zGQ0ShUTSlUvVtWh]{Warrior Born}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Leather Jack, Mail Shirt, Riding Horse with Saddle and Tack, Shield, Trade Tools (Farrier)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-up-in-arms.items.R8L5ZeyfYdK2G3qy]{Freelance Knight}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.F8NfBZdVSEIGCMtu]{Melee (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.sYbgpSnRqSZWgwFP]{Etiquette (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jQmIu8P85tF0njmD]{Seasoned Traveller}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.4MJJCiOKPkBByYwW]{Strike Mighty Blow}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.spdiWsONKTzkLbg3]{Stone Soup}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Destrier with Saddle and Tack, Melee Weapon (Any), Plate Armour and Helm, Personal Heraldry<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-up-in-arms.items.fUkza08rg5nl8XET]{Freelance Captain}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.7pQo66cESWttzIlb]{Gamble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.NDetl9BhAQBVnHKf]{Combat Master}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8oWhzlcw7oiHGMFu]{Unshakable}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.vCgEAetBMngR53aT]{War Leader}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Barding, Small Retinue of Followers<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-up-in-arms.items.yeEUFcS607PPA1Y0]{Knight Commander}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Battle)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.u0CFf3xwiyidD9T5]{Luck}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.DS44h27iCOvUBa4O]{Disarm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Company of knights, Squire<br /><br /></p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"_id":"TpwhRuvLbZT8gpQr","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.h7yDZkJj94QMA46z.JournalEntryPage.TpwhRuvLbZT8gpQr"}}},{"type":"text","name":"Fieldwarden","text":{"content":"<blockquote><p>Afternoon, Mrs. Bramblewine, how’s Alfie? Oh, that’s a shame, but I’m sure your amazing raspberry tarts will soon have his leg on the mend! What? Oh no, just doing my rounds, I couldn’t possibly… Oh well who am I to argue with the local Jam-making champion four years in a row and counting, eh? You know me, I go weak at the knees when I’m offered a bit o’ crumpet…”</p><p style=\"text-align:right\">– Bundlebrew Skelfsider, Greenleafs Fieldwarden</p></blockquote><p>Halflings prefer militias to standing armies, and have little apparent military strength to those unfamiliar with their ways. Visitors to the Moot often wonder at how the countryside and villages remain so peaceful and idyllic despite sharing a border with dread Sylvania where the dead never rest, with no obvious armies to repel them. A large part of the credit for this goes to the Field Wardens. These brave halflings patrol the borders of the Moot, using their intimate knowledge of the terrain and cunning guerrilla tactics to deter unwanted visitors. A Field Warden is first and foremost a Halfling of the people, a friendly face to reassure the public that all is well. They know every family in their area (and which baked treats they are likely to serve a Field Warden who happens to be passing by around tea time). It is a highly respected position, and any Field Warden can expect a busy off-duty calendar as families invite them to Bakeday meals, wedding feasts, funeral remembrance dinners or pie eating competitions. </p><p>Those attached to border patrols see much more in the way of action. The Moot is a fertile, bountiful place, and greatly coveted by bandits, greenskins and petty nobles who think themselves above province borders. Such intruders soon find the land is not as defenceless as it looked, and most beat a hasty retreat under a hail of expertly aimed sling stones from concealed Field Wardens. Along the Sylvanian border, Field Wardens are posted no longer than one week per month, to ensure none suffer the stress of the walking dead for too long. Even during times of “peace” with the Vampire Counts of Sylvania, most patrols are guaranteed to encounter at the very least a pack of rotting zombies shambling over the border. Due to this unsavoury but very necessary duty, veteran Field Wardens often surprise other adventurers (Priests and Witch Hunters are often very surprised indeed) with their experience in combating necromancy.</p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-archives1/assets/actors/fieldwarden.webp\" width=\"344\" height=\"436\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Halfling</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Ranger</p><h3 class=\"sidebar-title no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Fieldwarden Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-archives1.items.eTb72IpSFjQGwhBH]{Novice Warden}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Moot)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.KQjZ85kKz42YQGYT]{Ranged (Sling)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Xk5tp3aasPNtk4zt]{Stealth (Rural)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GU1KpgY3MeFIaDaq]{Careful Strike}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.MoiYSfJRPHu7SZCQ]{Distract}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.5eDd6iFeR9G6cCfz]{Fast Shot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.IogM5gnsoOX63w7j]{Stout-hearted}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Backpack, Tent, Map of local area, Sling with 10 stones, Trade Tools (as Trade)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-archives1.items.c4SxYRUNDABuu3Ru]{Field Warden}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.R2ytluHiEFF2KQ5e]{Consume Alcohol}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.COND1RfSn9v58QiN]{Secret Signs (Scout)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XIcDsaW4D8wScezw]{Accurate Shot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.J9MK0AIaTbvd5oF6]{Drilled}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.AcnFuDKRemLI9ey7]{Nose for Trouble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.afREA9q7v4Scuozn]{Orientation}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Leather Jack, Hand Weapon, Lantern with Oil<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-archives1.items.lFb44eROpT8Sr6To]{Field Warden Sergeant}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Necromancy)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.HngrTVqKis08Nvcf]{Set Trap}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.E3vTSCzgrasNijUO]{Fleet Footed}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zImcTgEl2XNnbu5W]{Hardy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x0WMGwuQzReXcQrs]{Night Vision}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Quality Mail Shirt, Squad of Novice Wardens<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-archives1.items.kwU1Ajl5GoBee34j]{Field Warden Captain}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 5<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.8pVzgPkgWpTJvfhG]{Fearless}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.E98mVLZgE8bX5vQW]{Hatred (Undead)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.WCXnFSV4WOSmzzc4]{Inspiring}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.nWLsoWQBCjPRKxYx]{Robust}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Moot terrain)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Garrison of Experienced Field Wardens, Respect of the Community<br /><br /></p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"title":{"level":1,"show":true},"sort":2600000,"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.eawkn4xfBfFW3sd6.JournalEntryPage.qFs945qryMKHavCn"}},"_id":"C0BkcpSqX0BvOgRj"},{"type":"text","name":"Karak Ranger","text":{"content":"<blockquote><p>“A guide? Aye, I suppose you could call us that, if a guide had to run twenty leagues, swim another ten, fight off a hungry ogre and climb to the peak of Karak Norn all before breakfast. Now pay up manling, or by Grimnir our caravan will be delivering its goods posthumously!”</p><p style=\"text-align:right\">-Snori Brakisson, on establishing a new trade route between Ubersreik and his clan in the Grey Mountains</p></blockquote><p>The remote mountain strongholds of the dwarfs are protected by all manner of dangerous terrain both above and below ground. A landslide might render a surface route impassable, and every year more underground territory is lost to the greenskins, or a once-safe bridge is torn down by the relentless gnawing of the Raki. It is the duty of the Karak Ranger to patrol these routes and keep them safe, or establish new paths where an old one has become too dangerous. A Karak Ranger’s survival hinges on preparedness; there is little company or comfort to be found along the ancient dark tunnels or secret mountain passes, and even less chance of help should he encounter danger. One must be prepared to leap large chasms, climb sheer surfaces, or cross large bodies of water (or sewage, or even lava), depending on the route. Every bush, every shadow, may contain dangers, waiting to pounce. A Karak Ranger must be tough and adaptable to survive, by turns able to hunt, scout, and fight, or even repair a bridge mid-expedition.</p><p>Karak Rangers often spend many months in the field, far away from civilisation. Where human or halfling rangers are often seen by society as becoming wild like nature itself (most dwarves believe elves were always uncivilised tree-lovers), a Karak Ranger remains true to his people; The mountains are brutal and unforgiving, and to live in “harmony” with them would be to abandon one’s traditions and clan, an unthinkable prospect. Karak Rangers seek to tame the wilds, not submit to them. Some Rangers train animal companions such as dogs, birds of prey or even hardy mountain goats, both for company and aid in scouting and hunting. </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-archives1/assets/actors/karak-ranger.webp\" width=\"330\" height=\"491\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Dwarf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Ranger</p><h3 class=\"sidebar-title no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Karak Ranger Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-archives1.items.fGgDpDWP5d0cDcWd]{Hold Runner}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.sRuMlaPU5xdIrwhd]{Climb}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CcNJsS4jSwB6Ug1J]{Endurance}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Cartographer)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.KL4pCOqma5E7fLG4]{Row}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.xx8SgdWYEjKct7ym]{Implacable}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.afREA9q7v4Scuozn]{Orientation}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1dUizIgLBgn4jICC]{Strider (any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.FF41XPboORgyDNsv]{Strong Back}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Backpack, Hand Weapon, Leather Jack, Trade tools (Cartographer)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-archives1.items.fRkh5R4ocyLgOwzO]{Karak Ranger}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.4IGdIhnwTaZijzg7]{Charm Animal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.H2upcZ7q7qAPtPic]{Ranged (Blackpowder)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.COND1RfSn9v58QiN]{Secret Signs (Scout)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.6l2JkMfD3mNxqiep]{Secret Signs (Ranger)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rt2rGSwFDCDHPh0A]{Track}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.4MJJCiOKPkBByYwW]{Strike Mighty Blow}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.MGEPI4jNhymNIRVz]{Scale Sheer Surface}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.AcnFuDKRemLI9ey7]{Nose for Trouble}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Blackpowder Weapon with Ammunition, Grappling Hook &amp; Rope<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-archives1.items.jixfk0Zo7MQDLGj9]{Karak Pathkeeper}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.osMw1Be6YgRBolTm]{Lore (Engineering)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cHbQeJQ7cVZZyDyl]{Stealth (Underground)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XIcDsaW4D8wScezw]{Accurate Shot}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.VscjNv6RzHFb9CQp]{Enclosed Fighter}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.PoYlemaEIbZw30Em]{River Guide} OR @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0ep8BNMiZGVLTHpr]{Gunner}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.CV9btQn09S9Fn8Jk]{Strong Legs}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Tools (Masonry)<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛ @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-archives1.items.Redw0hR56YLisVVs]{Karak Mountain Strider}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: <br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6lQRRgjz8IZH4bbV]{Tinker}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.580fwhKfOZJFxMID]{Savant (Dwarf Holds and Routes)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.nWLsoWQBCjPRKxYx]{Robust}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jviOQmy0luQOySC2]{Tenacious}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: 4 Apprentice Hold Runners, Maps, Souvenirs from many Travels.<br /><br /></p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"title":{"level":1,"show":true},"sort":3900000,"_id":"GIoxmaazR63VSdBw","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.eawkn4xfBfFW3sd6.JournalEntryPage.GIoxmaazR63VSdBw"}}},{"name":"Template","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p></p><p></p><p></p><p><strong>Species: </strong></p><p><strong>Class: </strong></p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Wrecker Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: <br /><strong>Skills</strong>:<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: <br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: <br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: <br /><strong>Skills</strong>: <br /><strong>Talents</strong>: <br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: <br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: <br /><strong>Skills</strong>: <br /><strong>Talents</strong>: <br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: <br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: <br /><strong>Skills</strong>: <br /><strong>Talents</strong>: <br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: <br /><br /></p>","markdown":""},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":8300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{}},"_id":"VZrOM13HDSO32zex"},{"name":"Wardancer","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>You are a follower of the dancer in shadows, the Archfey Loec.</em></p><div><div><div><p>Loec is the Archfey of Trickery, Music, Revelry, Shadows and Vengeance, he resides where the feywild and Shadowfel overlap over the Warding Woods. Loec is a mysterious figure because his followers guard the secrets of his rites and purpose behind a veil of secrecy. His servants are occasionally called Feastmasters for their part in the great festivals, where they lead the celebration and perform intricate dances that recount the history of the Warding Woods. Loec appears to the Elves as a lithe youth who dances across the void, and his laughter stirs the souls and spirits that dwell there. Without him, it is said, the heavens would grow dull and cold, for the stars of the night sky would no longer have reason to remain wakeful.</p></div><p>Fyr Darric, the Trickster's Wood, is a High Realm of the Warding Woods, ruled by Lady Heggria of the Masque. Fyr Darric is Loec the Trickster's holy ground within the Warding Woods, the site of many shrines to his anarchic glory. Here too can be found the Feast Halls of the Wardance — the closest thing that the nomadic Wardancers of the Warding Woods have to a home. As a result, the glades of Fyr Darric always resound to the sound of laughter, though much of it is mean-spirited. Every deception requires a victim, and the consequences can range from wounded pride to a slow death.</p><p>Never is this more true that at the Festivals of the Equinox, when captives are promised their freedom, if only they can slay a Wardancer in single combat. None succeed, of course, for the Devo-tees of Loec are peerless duellists. The true con-test is not for the victim’s freedom, but to see how many wounds the Wardancer can inflict before his foe expires. Any captive who dies to fewer than a hundred cuts is thought to be poor sport indeed.</p><p></p><p>Other Wood Elves regard the Wardancers as wild and unpredictable, and not without cause, for they are the servants and worshippers of the Elven trickster god, Loec. The Wardancers lead the Elves in music and rejoicing, and perform the intricate dance rituals that re-enact the history of the Warding Woods, a form of storytelling more im-portant to the Wood Elves than the more conventional method of writing.</p><p>To a Wardancer, even other Elves appear to be moving painfully slowly, for every move made by one of the kin of Loec flows into the next, and thence the next one after that without conscious thought or guidance. Forgoing armour, the Wardancers decorate themselves with swirling designs and dye their hair in bright colours, taking on the roles of mythical figures and ferocious warriors, their form of movement, and even their fighting style, paying homage to the one who inspires their dance.</p><p>Wardancers are sublime warriors, made even more deadly through their war dances. For these, the favoured rituals of the Trickster God, no rhythm is called nor are orders issued. Instead, the dancers instinctively enact a pattern of lethal movements, complementing the dances performed by the rest of the troupe. Each Wardancer leaps and pirouettes through the enemy ranks to music only she hears, gracefully evading her opponent’s clumsy blows and ending his life with an impossibly swift to strike of her own.</p><p>Shadowdancers are the closest thing that the Trickster God has to a priesthood, and they are both respected and feared as a result. Shadowdancers, and Shadowdancers only, know all the paths through the Warding Woods — indeed, it is said that they tread the paths of the Dreaming Wood as surely as they do the mortal world. In battle, they are even more dazzlingly swift than other Wardancers. At other times they are less flamboyant, preferring to confound others with deceptions of the mind rather than swiftness of body. Indeed, many Shadowdancers can create illusions, which they inevitably use to further distract their foes or mete out a much needed dose of humility to Elves or spirits that have forgotten their station.</p></div></div><p> </p><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-akoris/art/Fylneth.jpg\" /><p></p><p><strong>Species: </strong>Wood Elf</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Ranger</p><h3 style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"no-toc\">Wardancer Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"h