ext":{"content":"<blockquote><p> ‘ Yes, Horstmann’s betrayal marred us all — do not for a moment listen to those who claim that we bear no portion of the shame. He was a canker at the heart of our college, a rot that by shear luck did not spread as far as it might. In a generation or two we might shake off the shadow of what our former patriarch has done, but until that day we must bear responsibility for it.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— Hierophant Gertrude Langtrosser</em></p><p>‘Light can do one of two things — illuminate, or blind. Be sure to make good use of both.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— Unknown Hierophant to an acolyte</em></p></blockquote><p><em>You are a member of the Order of Light, respected for its difficult practise and regarded as exotic and austere.</em></p><p>Most common folk make no distinction between mages; they call them all ‘wizards’ (or less respectful names behind their backs). But among people who do make the distinction, Light Wizards are also known as white wizards, hierophants or, sometimes, exorcists.</p><p>These wizards usually dress in pristine white clothes, a colour that tends to attract the Light Wind. Any decorations are in silver or gold embroidery, referring to symbols of the order — the Serpent of Light, the Tree of Learning, or one of the many others. </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/light-wizard.webp\" width=\"296\" height=\"621\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p><h3 class=\"no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Hierophant Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.K9uKLWX1uQGVwlo9]{Acolyte of the Light Order}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.ChI09rjm2afh1bqI]{Channelling (Hysh)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Sing)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Nehekhara)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Candle with Holder, Grimoire, Staff<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.YgIzwVYLzUrU6Inr]{Hierophant}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Light)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.g3y373FnWJEAxgEB]{Detect Artefact}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.QsrXxGZiHjth7RMg]{Savvy}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Magical Licence, Practical Robes<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.qBujr65KnmXzYDR7]{Master Hierophant}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Daemonology)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.9tbHTeuvEMZrp0rx]{Research}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BYChSVfMG004eflQ]{Instinctive Diction}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.V9N0LMnXf1WYseCL]{Tower of Memories}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Acolyte Apprentice, Light Warhorse, Magical Item, Standard Robes<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.haDoPJq0R4WPPMdk]{Guardian of the Light Order}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.vMYEkrWj0ip6ZOdv]{Resistance (Chaos)}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Elaborate Robes, Library (Magic), Study<br /><br /></p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"_id":"L1HMS581Scz2IyCJ","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":3600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nsZAkSDjPteDuC82.JournalEntryPage.L1HMS581Scz2IyCJ"}}},{"name":"Alchemist","text":{"content":"<blockquote><p> ‘Far be it from me to diminish magisters of the other colleges, but one does wonder. Azyr? Heads in the clouds. Shyish? So depressing that a rose would wilt in their hands. Ghur? Well, let’s just say you should lay straw down on the floor. But we of the Gold College? We are practical, rational, dealing with the world as it is. And we make money. A lot of it.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— Magister Horst Bergmann</em></p><p>‘If any of you doubt that wizards are enemies of the people, look at Gold Wizards! Seekers after knowledge? With their fancy carriages and gold jewellery and potions they sell to the high and mighty for more than any of us see in a year? Bah! They know the secret of making gold and refuse to share it with the People! I say down with them all!’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-altdorf.journals.rSRadYoaNXkEq8gs.JournalEntryPage.F6TqV2NzkEUQYOcg#plant]{PLANT} (Popular League Against Nobility and Taxation) agitator Benno Metzger</em></p></blockquote><p><em>You are a member of the Gold Order, widely acknowledged as masters of the manipulation of matter.</em></p><p>Like the astromancers of the Celestial Order, the magister-alchemists of the Gold Wind have a scientific, intellectual reputation. But, whereas the students of Azyr peer into the heavens for signs of possible futures and indulge themselves in abstruse theoretical debates, the alchemists focus on practical research, with applications in the physical world.</p><p> </p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/gold-wizard.webp\" width=\"320\" height=\"439\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p><h3 class=\"no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Alchemist Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.5gdO9Qh6GmxPaiUT]{Alchemist Apprentice}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.QJ1sfMkNmIh04nky]{Channelling (Chamon)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pKLMbmG3Ivt6mzMf]{Haggle}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Alchemist)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Grimoire, Staff<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.AP06mXK4djaTPgDf]{Alchemist}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.nLlRDNRC95plBgXs]{Lore (Metallurgy)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.9tbHTeuvEMZrp0rx]{Research}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Blacksmith or Goldsmith or Engineer)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Metal)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.41JhsSNW1Ttza3JK]{Argumentative}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.g3y373FnWJEAxgEB]{Detect Artefact}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Magical Licence, Portable Alchemical Laboratory, Practical Robes<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.CORrT86L4a6BIGfZ]{Master Alchemist}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.osMw1Be6YgRBolTm]{Lore (Engineering)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.7ToyUcqJDkceoJRd]{Lore (Science)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.wKwel9MG7NIG3i3w]{Trade (Engineer)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.zv3IyoU2wkPZu8pD]{Bookish}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GRRN3XAKIpEVCY7z]{Craftsman (Blacksmith or Goldsmith or Engineer)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BYChSVfMG004eflQ]{Instinctive Diction}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Alchemist Apprentice, Light Warhorse, Magical Item, Standard Robes<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.cSj5RYWSPwuF3wqS]{Alchemist Lord}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XzPlUWFDtOOjG98P]{Language (Khazalid)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.F2EiuAc6IpaGd4J7]{War Wizard}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OROfMcVqRnZHINkU]{Wealthy}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Elaborate Robes, Library (Engineering, Magic, or Science), Workshop (Engineering or Magic)<br /><br /></p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-wom/assets/misc/spot-chamon.webp\" width=\"250\" height=\"121\" /></div>","format":1,"markdown":""},"_id":"aYYDra6LCt6daz0s","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nsZAkSDjPteDuC82.JournalEntryPage.aYYDra6LCt6daz0s"}}},{"name":"Druid","text":{"content":"<blockquote><p> ‘The spiral is the symbol of life. Such a spiral stands for the coiled secret in each of us — that everything we can be is written within us, like a code. It can only be solved through the insight of Ghyran.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>Friedric— h Miescher, Jade Wizard</em></p><p>‘Had one of those druids in the other day. Not sure what she was up to, but when I made the bed the next day, it was full of leaves.’</p><p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— Arnold Fleiss, innkeeper</em></p></blockquote><p><em>You tap the vitality of the earth and the power of nature to manipulate the natural world through your magic.</em></p><p>Jade Wizards are more welcome in villages across the Empire than any of the other Imperial Wizards. It is well known they can control plants, and that the land thrives in their presence. Any settlement that welcomes a druid should expect a bumper harvest in the coming year.</p><p>If a crop is devastated by pestilence the people are likely to pray to Sigmar and Rhya but the authorities might contact the Jade College for magical aid. The Jade College treats these requests rather judiciously as they resent being seen as the farmers of the Empire and will only respond to very extreme or decidedly supernatural blights. It is still a common enough job, however, for the aspiring Jade Wizard, to travel to assist those who work the land. Many druids are knowledgeable of the practical elements of agriculture as well as the magical, serving as teacher as much as magister.</p><p>The college supplies battle wizards to the Empire’s armies. @UUID[.MVwOuM2YKhUvA1E1#the-jade-college]{The Jade College} believes their service goes under-appreciated; the military imagination is lacking when compared to the magical one. What could be more useful to an army on the march than surreptitious and untraceable movement through difficult terrain? Unfortunately the Empire’s generals are more likely to have a wizard set fire to something instead.</p><p>Jade Wizards are usually encouraged to make their own way in the world. They often travel in the hope of encountering interesting and new natural phenomena, like flora that might be useful for cures or as magical ingredients.</p><div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-wom/assets/actors/jade-wizard1.webp\" width=\"283\" height=\"728\" /></div><p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p><p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p><h3 class=\"no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Druid Advance Scheme</h3><table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♛</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td><td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td></tr></tbody></table><h3><strong>✠. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.6MH5Q21LCV7bLIZo]{Druid’s Apprentice}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLSVcLqPvnd1cg4U]{Channelling (Ghyran)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.4IGdIhnwTaZijzg7]{Charm Animal}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.os4NKy5Oy6sRt1eh]{Outdoor Survival}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Copper Sickle, Grimoire, Staff<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♟. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.1TQKLOYtHNmBs4kL]{Druid}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Battle)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Life)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.g3y373FnWJEAxgEB]{Detect Artefact}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9sMAf0xmehjEmUao]{Fast Hands}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Magical Licence, Practical Robes, Silver Sickle<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♜. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.Iko57bxHxRkuRh5i]{Master Druid}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.MXy22hFCgntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Plants)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BYChSVfMG004eflQ]{Instinctive Diction}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.q58lK4kULJZB5GjE]{Rover}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Gold Sickle, Magical Item, Standard Robes<br /><br /></p><h3><strong>♛. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.98bbvccaFbdk8caf]{Druid Lord}</strong></h3><p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.F2EiuAc6IpaGd4J7]{War Wizard}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Elaborate Robes, Garden Retreat, Library (Magic)<br /><br /></p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"_id":"KGWoTLSkr4Gj2AlR","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":2050000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nsZAkSDjPteDuC82.JournalEntryPage.KGWoTLSkr4Gj2AlR"}}},{"name":"Astromancer","text":{"content":"<blockquote>\n<p> ‘Normally I would trust a wizard as far as he can swim with an anchor round his neck, but it’s been handy having Magister Aeolus aboard. Granted he charges a pretty penny and dresses a little fancy for a commoner, but he knows how to talk to his betters, can scry heavy weather, and saved our souls with his lightning when those Skaeling reavers attacked.’</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— Admiral Klaus von Nesselzelt of the Imperial Navy</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><em>You scrutinise the heavens and draw down the Wind of Azyr to bend the elements to your will and manipulate fate itself.</em></p>\n<p>Magisters who channel <em>Azyr</em> are astromancers, also known as Celestial Wizards, or ‘Blue Wizards’ by the uneducated. They favour skullcaps, high-collared cloaks, and expensive robes in deep blues and blacks, emblazoned with silver and gold motifs to represent the night sky. Somewhere on their person they wear the symbol of their order, the Comet of Power. Many present a well-groomed, aloof appearance to the world.</p>\n<p>Each magister carries a staff, usually topped with an ornamental telescope, miniature orrery, or armillary sphere. Sometimes these are functional, but they primarily serve as a symbolic badge of the Astromancer’s art.</p>\n<p>Progression through the ranks of the Celestial College is orderly, like the arrangement of the night sky. After passing rigorous exams, new apprentices (called acolytes) are expected to serve their master without complaint — taking observations, readying instruments, fetching tomes, uncovering research, and undertaking any menial task that an astromancer considers beneath them.</p>\n<p>The most perilous and humiliating chore is cleaning the college’s glass domes of bird droppings. When their master does not want to travel, acolytes may be sent on long distance errands to check an obscure detail from a premonition or to witness a meteorological phenomenon.</p>\n<div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/celestial-wizard.webp\" width=\"309\" height=\"514\" /></div>\n<p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p>\n<p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p>\n<h3 class=\"no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Astromancer Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>✠. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.RsfJtwwXVAAGkFFD]{Celestial Acolyte}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.GlcVY8MTqHTS1JWX]{Augury}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.hpc8g8Z9rl3fJECS]{Channelling (Azyr)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Fortune Telling)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Grimoire, Staff, Starwatcher’s Handbook<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♟. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.1QuE5fMFyyAFvZIv]{Astromancer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 4<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Battle)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Astronomy)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.9tbHTeuvEMZrp0rx]{Research}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Heavens)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.g3y373FnWJEAxgEB]{Detect Artefact}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.afREA9q7v4Scuozn]{Orientation}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Ceremonial Telescope, Magical Licence, Practical Robes, Sextant<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♜. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.4aT4HISK4oxRCIXv]{Grand Astromancer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zZUX7wO4rOo8k9F0]{Navigation}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Prophecy)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BYChSVfMG004eflQ]{Instinctive Diction}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.jQmIu8P85tF0njmD]{Seasoned Traveller}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.SHH2vUpNxj0wmmPT]{Well-prepared}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Expensive Orrery or Armillary Sphere, Light Warhorse, Magical Item, Standard Robes<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♛. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.C3NIR6HoI0iLoXop]{Lord Celestial}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.x0WMGwuQzReXcQrs]{Night Vision}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.F2EiuAc6IpaGd4J7]{War Wizard}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Elaborate Robes, Library (Magic), Tower or Mountaintop Observatory<br /><br /></p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"_id":"EpHoISPX7OlMGttN","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nsZAkSDjPteDuC82.JournalEntryPage.EpHoISPX7OlMGttN"}}},{"name":"Shadowmancer","text":{"content":"<blockquote>\n<p> ‘Truth is so valuable that it needs to be swathed in a cloak of deceit.’</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— Reiner Stark, Magister Patriarch of the Grey Order</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><em>Secretive and deceitful, you combine the abilities of wizard and spy.</em></p>\n<p>The only thing a Grey Wizard is certain of is that nothing is certain in this world, and that things are rarely as they seem. They know that lies often cover up other lies and become so used to falsehood and deception that they have trouble recognizing the truth as it is.</p>\n<p>Shadowmancers are distrustful people, who rarely believe what they see at face value and always look for false bottoms, hidden meanings, and concealed motives. In return, they are careful to withold their own beliefs and intentions. Truth has value, they’ve learned, and items of value shouldn’t be just given away.</p>\n<p>Despite their natural mistrust, they are good diplomats and spies. Many Grey Wizards work at noble courts, in mercantile houses, or in criminal organisations — although often in a different profession, keeping their identity as a wizard hidden. Sometimes they even maintain two or more roles at the same time. Shadowmancers are masters of disguise and adept at maintaining several identities. At the same time they are socially adept and can relate to people — if only because that makes it easier to deceive them.</p>\n<p>Grey Wizards don’t spend much time at their college grounds in Altdorf. Those who are not engaged in cloak and dagger plots prefer to travel throughout the Empire, and even across its borders. Doing so permits them to learn about the state of the Empire and assess the dangers that threaten it from within. Grey Guardians travelling the Empire often arrange to meet their colleagues at particular places at certain days of the year. Sometimes it’s just an encounter between two travellers, other times a group of shadowmancers gather for a few days at an inn or out in the fields. During these encounters and gatherings the wizards share information they’ve learned, and in doing so, get a more complete image of whatever threats exist.</p>\n<div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/shadow-wizard.webp\" width=\"340\" height=\"460\" /></div>\n<p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p>\n<p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p>\n<h3 class=\"no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Shadowmancer Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">♜</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>✠. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.pVPz88X8CW3iELbf]{Trickster’s Apprentice}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e6uURn9IFt09beNU]{Channelling (Ulgu)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.CJxLsDRzVMguEpF1]{Secret Signs (Grey Order)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.zkI6tIqbyAZvh0Th]{Stealth (Urban)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Grimoire, Hooded Cloak, Staff<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♟. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.jRxK82URXmYjFor2]{Shadowmancer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.0CwV96kTDRF0jUhk]{Entertain (Acting)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Shadows)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.g3y373FnWJEAxgEB]{Detect Artefact}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9sMAf0xmehjEmUao]{Fast Hands}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Magical Licence, Practical Robes<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♜. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.fmRCvVfzwjzFhePw]{Grey Guardian}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Politics)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.9tbHTeuvEMZrp0rx]{Research}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.77p3QRKgFWakkndF]{Blather}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BYChSVfMG004eflQ]{Instinctive Diction}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.LU6Ycl5z4kp1Wr04]{Mimic}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Light Warhorse, Magical Item, Standard Robes<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♛. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.SPMrBkpmOi42ErQZ]{Grey Lord}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.PJ4oxDExnuFNr2Fi]{Secret Identity}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.XSb3QVB9ipPBFt56]{Shadow}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.V9N0LMnXf1WYseCL]{Tower of Memories}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.F2EiuAc6IpaGd4J7]{War Wizard}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Elaborate Robes, Library (Magic), Ring of Informers, Workshop (Magic)<br /><br /></p>\n<div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-wom/assets/misc/spot-ulgu.webp\" width=\"310\" height=\"98\" /></div>","format":1,"markdown":""},"_id":"eZxfheujk03euEN4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":6700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nsZAkSDjPteDuC82.JournalEntryPage.eZxfheujk03euEN4"}}},{"name":"Pyromancer","text":{"content":"<blockquote>\n<p> ‘Power is the key, and the key is the symbol, and the symbol is a metaphor, and a metaphor is perspective, and perspective is control, and control is power...’</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Litany of Control, Red Book of Aqshy</em></p>\n<p>‘They’re not all like that, full of fire and bluster. We had one in last year who cooked us a lovely roast duck with the power of his mind. Lovely it was. Of course, the next morning, we discovered he’d burned down our barn.’</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>– Arnold Fleiss, Innkeeper</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><em>You feed off your raw passion and emotional energy to bring magical firepower to the battlefield.</em></p>\n<p>Bright Wizards are the most belligerent of all the wizards of the Empire. This is common knowledge. Though other colleges are known for their particular sort of aggression, and all serve the military in one capacity or another, the Bright College brings shock and awe to the battlefield like none other. This reputation may lack nuance and be the result of unsophisticated accounts by common soldiers and fraught enemies, but it is steeped in truth. The Bright Wizards often adopt a warlike and fearsome appearance, their staffs made of iron and topped with a brazier ready to wield all-consuming flame.</p>\n<p>The Bright Wind is also associated with emotion. Passion bordering on anger seems to drive Bright Wizards. Part of learning to be a pyromancer is to allow one’s emotions to run free, to enable the gathering of <em>Aqshy</em>. But the key to real power as a Bright Wizard is knowing how to master passion, knowing where to draw the line, and being able to stop oneself from being consumed by such seductive power. Practices to aid control are a large part of the wizard’s training.</p>\n<p>To help with such discipline and self-control and to engender humility, apprentices spend the first period of their apprenticeship undertaking the most menial of chores. They are required to stoke the furnaces that continually burn within the depths of the college, and to scrub the soot encrusted chambers at the heart of the complex. They carry sacks of coal through the building and shovel it into giant hoppers. They must meticulously maintain the mundane paraphernalia that ultimately underlies all the magical functions of the college. This period might be boring and laborious, but it necessitates rest and recuperation which in turn allows an apprentice some time to themselves to savour the delights of Altdorf.</p>\n<div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/bright-wizard.webp\" width=\"354\" height=\"564\" /></div>\n<p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p>\n<p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p>\n<h3 class=\"no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Pyromancer Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">T</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">I</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Agi</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Dex</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Int</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">WP</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">Fel</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♜</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♟</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\"> </td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">✠</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align:center\">♛</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>✠. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.J0HmTlsLVtkCPRh7]{Apprentice Pyromancer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Brass 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.gh91jaxzTBgbMoi5]{Channelling (Aqshy)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.1jCxbFAUuFuAPLJl]{Dodge}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.I0yPc4PH5erWJLmu]{Intimidate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.cYtU0ORRFCOpQLWz]{Intuition}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Battle)}, <em>@UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.e3McIND4Rrsn5cE6]{Language (Magick)}</em>, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Magic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.rOPmyLWa37e7s9v6]{Melee (Basic)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.PzimjNx9Ojq4g6mV]{Melee (Polearm)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.Fs06sr7y9JKpVQmB]{Perception}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.1IZWRr7BYOIcqPlQ]{Aethyric Attunement}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mdPGZsn2396dEpOf]{Petty Magic}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.GogGbYxkVdCmiKqf]{Read/Write}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.OEjUvJKi0xmBwbS2]{Second Sight}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: First Key of Secrets, Grimoire, Staff<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♟. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.i4Y4UeCkLIWvy98a]{Pyromancer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Silver 3<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.exLrBrn2mjb6x2Cq]{Charm}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.pxNjTxsp1Kp0SmQe]{Cool}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.RLQHm1s4IuY9RSr2]{Gossip}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oMaJZ5cvCJeOUq9H]{Leadership}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Warfare)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.3O9clK7LGyuLTHPW]{Arcane Magic (Lore of Fire)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.g3y373FnWJEAxgEB]{Detect Artefact}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.9sMAf0xmehjEmUao]{Fast Hands}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mNoCuaVbFBflfO6X]{Sixth Sense}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Magical Licence, Practical Robes, Second and Third Keys of Secrets, Sword<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♜. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.Y1mkEiA6meXtAjhK]{Master Pyromancer}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 1<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.MXy22hFCgntdlQrn]{Animal Care}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.bSWoV1IiS5qWNw39]{Evaluate}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.9tbHTeuvEMZrp0rx]{Research}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.oSbEE6eXH1S3LfUU]{Ride (Horse)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.URwIDtInCsxOoGqM]{Dual Wielder}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.BYChSVfMG004eflQ]{Instinctive Diction}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.6w30u0VPsAicrqb5]{Magical Sense}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0hn6UaKq8CoZP2zD]{Menacing}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Fourth and Fifth Keys of Secrets, Light Warhorse, Magical Item, Standard Robes<br /><br /></p>\n<h3><strong>♛. @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-wom.items.Nc8VO7Uo1JFUpA1I]{Pyromancer Lord}</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Status</strong>: Gold 2<br /><strong>Skills</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.XQiiwS9m2Du1IMUz]{Language (Any)}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.skills.DRO5DLF6UcfkvNSh]{Lore (Any)}<br /><strong>Talents</strong>: @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.0LdHytqyNmg2pcAX]{Combat Aware}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mqo51ORnxijcqNNu]{Frightening}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.mgeiaDZXei7JBEgo]{Iron Will}, @UUID[Compendium.wfrp4e-core.talents.F2EiuAc6IpaGd4J7]{War Wizard}<br /><strong>Trappings</strong>: Apprentice, Elaborate Robes, Library (Magic), Sixth and Seventh Keys of Secrets, Workshop (Magic)<br /><br /></p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"_id":"itwBfr0GHErukQ3E","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":5700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.nsZAkSDjPteDuC82.JournalEntryPage.itwBfr0GHErukQ3E"}}},{"name":"Shaman","text":{"content":"<blockquote>\n<p> ‘The Amber College is outside the city.’</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— Shaman riddle</em></p>\n<p>‘Had one of those shamans in the other day. He ended up sleeping in the stable. I was gonna let him stay for free, but he said it was the best room in the Inn. So I charged him the same price as the luxury suite.’</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>— Arnold Fleiss, Innkeeper</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><em>Ruled by your magical affinity you are drawn instinctively to the wild places and its great beasts.</em></p>\n<p>Amber Wizards are known for their feral appearance and lifestyle, more at home in the wilderness than the town, and with more affinity for animals than their fellow Humans. Many wander the Empire’s vast untamed landscape, but just as many find a place they like and settle there. Every village in the Empire has a story of a local monster, giant, or witch who lives in the forest and is to be feared but is seldom encountered. More often than not, this is an Amber Wizard.</p>\n<p>Some wizards do interact and cooperate with the people of nearby villages. Though they are more comfortable on their own and loathe to be disturbed, many are kind enough to help and advise local communities when they need it. The superstitious folk of the Empire, being what they are, often shun the Amber Wizards in return.</p>\n<p>Just as there is little formal hierarchy within the Amber Order, there is no formal system for entering it as an apprentice. Wizards are always on the lookout for potential apprentices, those with a spark of the magical about them and an instinct for the wild. Some wizards even steal babies from the crib, they say. More likely, if a shaman comes across a potential young recruit, they will reach an agreement with their parents to take them on. However feared wizards might be among the folk of the Empire, few parents are not going to feel some sort of pride and accomplishment if their offspring is raised into such lofty ranks.</p>\n<div class=\"journal-image centered\"><img src=\"modules/wfrp4e-core/art/careers/amber-wizard.webp\" width=\"327\" height=\"585\" /></div>\n<p><strong>Species: </strong>Human</p>\n<p><strong>Class: </strong>Academics</p>\n<h3 class=\"no-toc\" style=\"text-align:center\">Shaman Advance Scheme</h3>\n<table style=\"height:34px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">WS</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">BS</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:60px;text-align:center\">S</td>\n<td style=\"height:17px;width:61px;text-align